(49, 1, 'hrbeu', 1, 'University Culture', '2009-04-26 23:46:59', '2009-05-13 18:06:20', 'hrbeu', 'University Culture', 'The school newspaper was released on September 1st 1953. Chairman Mao was invited by principal Chenggeng from Zhongnanhai and entitled the newspaper "Gongxue" (Engineering).', '<p><span style="font-family: Arial">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div id="imgBox">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>\r\n<table id="table1" bordercolor="#808080" cellpadding="0" width="100%" align="center" border="0" style="border-collapse: collapse">\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 200px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt"><img height="247" alt="" hspace="10" width="136" align="center" vspace="10" border="0" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/University_Culture/image002.gif" /></span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 511px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">University Newspaper</span></b></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">The school newspaper was released on September 1<sup>st</sup> 1953. Chairman Mao was invited by principal Chenggeng from Zhongnanhai and entitled the newspaper &quot;Gongxue&quot; (Engineering).</span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 200px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt"><img height="145" alt="" hspace="10" width="150" align="center" vspace="10" border="0" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/University_Culture/image003.jpg" /> </span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 511px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">University Emblem</span></b></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">Our emblem contains rich connotations. It combines gracefulness with elegance and represents the university''s distinctive features. Specifically, the meanings attached to the emblem can be seen as follows:</span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">First, the emblem is a complete round using the color of blue in three shades to symbolize the ocean, vividly presenting the university''s strength in the fields of ship industry, ocean equipment and exploration, and nuclear application as well as its dedication to these fields.</span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">Second, the change in blue from light shade in the center to dark shade on the outskirts symbolizes that HEU shoulders the historic responsibility to assist Chinese maritime undertakings on the road from offshore to deep ocean.</span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">Third, the Chinese characters &quot;<img height="23" alt="" width="116" align="top" border="0" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/University_Culture/heu.JPG" />&quot; at the top of the emblem represent the regard from the CPC and State, while the English name &quot;HARBIN ENGINEERING UNIVERSITY&quot; embodies the aspiration and determination of HEU to integrate with the world in order to establish a national elite as well as worldwide famous university.&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">Fourth, right in the middle part shows the symbolic figure of the 31st building and &quot;1953&quot; which is the year the PLA Military Engineering Institute was founded. They are set in a background light of baby blue to create a halo effect, symbolizing HEU has inherited the fine tradition of the PLA Military Engineering Institute and is striding into the future vigorously.</span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">Last but not least, the emblem is well-designed, beautifully-colored, and truly expressive. The structure of the emblem gives a sense of wholeness, symbolizing the solidarity, cohesiveness and harmony between teachers and students, their pursuit of a bright future and also their confidence and initiative in constructing a high-level research university </span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 200px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt"><img height="90" alt="" hspace="10" width="132" align="middle" vspace="10" border="0" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/University_Culture/image005.jpg" /></span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span lang="EN-US"><img height="130" alt="" hspace="10" width="99" align="middle" vspace="10" border="0" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/University_Culture/image007.jpg" /> </span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 511px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">University Flag</span></b></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">On January 13<sup>th</sup>, 2005, the attendants of the teachers'' congress standing presidium meeting reached a consensus on the final scheme for choosing the school flag. Our school flag was officially born. School flag is one of the important symbols for a university, and also constitutes a significant part of cultural construction of the university. Our school flag follows a simple pattern, terse, clear, and easy to recognize. The flag is in blue color, the color of the ocean, to symbolize the university''s strength in the fields of ship industry, ocean equipment and exploration, and nuclear application as well as its dedication to these fields. &quot;<img height="23" alt="" width="116" align="top" border="0" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/University_Culture/heu.JPG" />&quot; on the flag is in Chinese Maoti script which is our all-time script used for publicizing the university. Four kinds of school flag have been made: desk flag, flag row, hold flag, hanging flag. Desk flags are usually placed at desks in administrative offices and department offices. Flag row usually uses red, blue, orange, green and purple and is put out on big occasions. For hold flag and hanging flag, they are hung up in important indoor or outdoor places and used for external activities. </span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">Standard Size for Hold Flag and Hanging Flag:</span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">No 1:&nbsp; 288cm </span><span style="font-size: 12pt">x</span><span style="font-size: 12pt"><span lang="EN-US">192cm&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No 2:&nbsp; 240cm</span> x<span lang="EN-US">160cm&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No 3: 192cm</span> x<span lang="EN-US">128cm&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="IT" style="font-size: 12pt">No 4:&nbsp; 144cm</span> x<span lang="IT" style="font-size: 12pt">96cm&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;No 5:&nbsp; 96cm</span><span style="font-size: 12pt"> x</span><span lang="IT" style="font-size: 12pt">64cm</span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">Standard Size for Flag Row:</span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">60cm</span><span style="font-size: 12pt"> x</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">40cm</span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="NO-BOK" style="font-size: 12pt">Standard Size for Desk Flag:</span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="IT" style="font-size: 12pt">No1: 30cm</span><span style="font-size: 12pt"> x<span lang="IT">20cm&nbsp;&nbsp; No2: 21cm</span> x<span lang="IT">14cm&nbsp;&nbsp; No3: 18cm</span> x<span lang="IT">12cm&nbsp; No4: 12cm</span> x<span lang="IT">8cm</span></span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr style="height: 358.5pt">\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 200px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid; height: 358.5pt">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US"><font size="3"><img alt="" hspace="10" align="middle" vspace="10" border="0" style="width: 191px; height: 361px" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/University_Culture/image009.jpg" /></font></span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 511px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid; height: 358.5pt">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">University Anthem </span></b></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; On April 4<sup>th</sup>, 2006, the attendants of the teachers'' congress standing presidium meeting reached a consensus on the selection of school anthem. The song composed by Wangchijiu and Liukexin, members of the Song and Dance Ensemble of the Naval Political Department, was chosen as our school anthem.</span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The lyrics are profoundly meaningful, symbolic, and concise, embodying the long process of historic and cultural accumulation in HEU. In the lyrics, some images like &quot;military engineering&quot;, &quot;bugle&quot;, &quot;black soil&quot;, &quot;cyan eaves and jade tiles&quot; all refer to HEU''s unique characteristics. In the first paragraph of the verse, the image &quot;cathedral of military engineering&quot; and the image &quot;cradle of elites&quot; represent the PLA Military Engineering Institute and HEU respectively. Since there is a whole span of over half a century between PLA Military Engineering Institute and HEU, these two images vividly convey that HEU has traversed a great historic course of 54 years and cultivated many backbones of our country. The second paragraph is highlighted by &quot;growing with the sounds of bugle and learning at the Songhua River&quot;, which is a nice picture but more importantly the particular feeling in any HEU student who has a big heart and deep love towards their Alma Mater. And the chorus brings out to the fullest the spirit and determination in HEU students to be devoted to the undertakings of coastal defense regardless of difficulty and hardship.</span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">The tune of the anthem gives a feeling of firmness, determination, sacredness and solemnity, showing some tinge of a march. The verse part has a smooth melody, proceeding in steady major, depicting the past and present of HEU. In the beginning bars of the chorus part, the soft melody in minor brings out valuable work ethics and precise research quality in our teaching staff. Then the anthem goes to major key and enters its climax where our motto is impressively belted out. Finally, the anthem concludes with strong rhythmic notes.</span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr style="height: 186.9pt">\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 200px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid; height: 186.9pt"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">\r\n            <div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n            <div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n            <div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n            <div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n            <div id="imgBox"><a target="PhotoView" href="http://gongxue.cn/gongxueyingxiang/UploadFiles_5932/200611/20061107111541225.jpg"><img alt="" border="0" onload="if(this.width&gt;800) this.width=800" style="width: 194px; height: 170px" src="http://gongxue.cn/gongxueyingxiang/UploadFiles_5932/200611/20061107111541225.jpg" /></a></div>\r\n            </span></span></td>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 511px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid; height: 186.9pt">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">Roads on Campus</span></b></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal" align="left" style="text-align: left"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">On 11<sup>th</sup> July 2003, the 50<sup>th</sup> anniversary of HEU, names for roads on campus were officially settled. The 8 main roads on campus were named &quot;Donghai&quot;, &quot;Nanhai&quot;, &quot;Beihai&quot;, &quot;Xihai&quot;, &quot;Chengeng&quot;, &quot;Shichang&quot;, &quot;Aoliehuofu&quot;, &quot;Zhenghe&quot;, respectively. And the playfield was named &quot;military engineering playfield&quot;. </span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">The names of the four roads around &quot;Jungong Playfield&quot; reflect HEU''s devotion to sea transportation, coastal defense, and other undertakings related to the sea as its one distinctive feature, and also symbolize HEU''s long-cherished aspiration to go to the world. In addition, &quot;hai&quot; means the sea, since the sea is deep and immense, using &quot;sea&quot; in the names of the four roads also implies the vitality and eternity attached to HEU. And the other four roads are named after figures that are important in the course of our history and development. </span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr style="height: 78pt">\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 200px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid; height: 78pt"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">\r\n            <div id="imgBox"><a target="PhotoView" href="http://gongxue.cn/gongxueyingxiang/UploadFiles_5932/200609/20060927192530474.jpg"><img alt="" border="0" onload="if(this.width&gt;800) this.width=800" style="width: 167px; height: 100px" src="http://gongxue.cn/gongxueyingxiang/UploadFiles_5932/200609/20060927192530474.jpg" /></a></div>\r\n            <div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n            </span></span></td>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 511px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid; height: 78pt">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">The Chengeng Road, which runs from the south to north of HEU, is named in honor of the General Chengeng, the first principal of the PLA Military Engineering Institute, conveying a message of fulfilling the unrealized will of forefathers and building a bright future. </span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr style="height: 78pt">\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 200px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid; height: 78pt"><img alt="" style="width: 175px; height: 90px" src="http://gongxue.cn/gongxueyingxiang/UploadFiles_5932/200609/20060928235753718.jpg" /></td>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 511px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid; height: 78pt">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">The Shichang Road is named in honor of the hero Dengshichang in the Battle of Yalu River, the largest naval engagement of the First Sino-Japanese War in Qing Dynasty. Using &quot;Shichang&quot; as the road name aims at warning current generation as well as future generations to work diligently to serve the coastal defense. At the same time, since &quot;Shichang&quot; in Chinese means being prosperous forever, it symbolizes HEU will be strong and thriving at all times. </span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr style="height: 78pt">\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 200px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid; height: 78pt"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">\r\n            <div id="imgBox"><a target="PhotoView" href="http://gongxue.cn/gongxueyingxiang/UploadFiles_5932/200610/20061019102501181.jpg"><img alt="" border="0" onload="if(this.width&gt;800) this.width=800" style="width: 185px; height: 84px" src="http://gongxue.cn/gongxueyingxiang/UploadFiles_5932/200610/20061019102501181.jpg" /></a></div>\r\n            <div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n            </span></span></td>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 511px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid; height: 78pt">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">The <img height="17" alt="" width="89" align="middle" border="0" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/University_Culture/olhf.JPG" />Road is named after the chief consultant <img height="17" alt="" width="89" align="middle" border="0" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/University_Culture/olhf.JPG" />of the PLA Military Engineering Institute. This aims at commemorating the friendship and contributions to the founding of PLA Military Engineering Institute by Soviet Consultant Delegation and implying that at the start Military Engineering Institute kept pace with the world and today HEU will continue to accelerate the process of internationalization. </span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr style="height: 78pt">\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 200px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid; height: 78pt"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">\r\n            <div id="imgBox"><a target="PhotoView" href="http://gongxue.cn/gongxueyingxiang/UploadFiles_5932/200610/20061030190608403.jpg"><img alt="" border="0" onload="if(this.width&gt;800) this.width=800" style="width: 195px; height: 99px" src="http://gongxue.cn/gongxueyingxiang/UploadFiles_5932/200610/20061030190608403.jpg" /></a></div>\r\n            <div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n            </span></span></td>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 511px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid; height: 78pt">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">The Zhenghe Road is named after the historic figure Zhenghe, who made voyages to the Atlantic Ocean seven times when the Chinese navy was at its strongest. This aims at inspiring HEU teachers and students to strive for building a strong navy and for</span><span lang="EN-US"><font size="3"> </font></span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">the great rejuvenation of the Chinese nation.</span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr style="height: 123.75pt">\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 200px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid; height: 123.75pt">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align: center"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n            <span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">\r\n            <div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n            <div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n            <div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n            <div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n            <div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n            <div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n            <div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n            <div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n            <div id="imgBox"><a target="PhotoView" href="http://gongxue.cn/gongxueyingxiang/UploadFiles_5932/200610/20061019101454335.jpg"><img alt="" border="0" onload="if(this.width&gt;800) this.width=800" style="width: 196px; height: 349px" src="http://gongxue.cn/gongxueyingxiang/UploadFiles_5932/200610/20061019101454335.jpg" /></a></div>\r\n            </span></span></td>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 511px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid; height: 123.75pt">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">Bronze Statue of Chengeng</span></b></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">Chengeng(1903-1961)</span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">Chengeng was born on 27<sup>th</sup> February 1903 in the Xiangxiang county of Hunan province, prominent proletarian revolutionist, militarist, and preeminent leader of PLA. Chengeng was one of the chief founders of the undertakings of national defense technology and education in New China, and the first principal and commissar of the PLA Military Engineering Institute. He joined CCP in 1922, studied at the Huangpu Military Academy when it for the first time enrolled students. Upon graduation, he stayed at the academy as vice captain and company commander, and joined in putting down the rebellion of commercial corps and the punitive east expedition against Chenjiongming. In 1926, he went to Soviet to study and came back the next year to join the Nanchang Uprising as Camp Captain. Later, he went to Shanghai and engaged in information work in the organs of the CCP Central Committee. During the period of the Agrarian Revolutionary War, he was colonel and division commander of the fourth front army of Chinese Workers'' and Peasants'' Red Army, principal of the College of Red Army Infantry, colonel of the Red Army Cadre Regimental, and division commander of the first division of the first corps of Red Army. He also joined the Long March. During the period of Anti-Japanese War, he was brigadier of the 386<sup>th</sup> brigade of the 129<sup>th</sup> division of the Eighth Route Army, and commander of the Taiyue army of the Taiyue Military Region. During the period of Liberation War, he was commander of the fourth army of the Jin-Ji-Lu-Yu field army, commander and commissar of the fourth corps of the second field army of PLA. After the People''s Republic of China was founded, he served as vice commander of the Xinan Military Region, commander of the Yunnan Military Region, and chairman of Yunnan Provincial People''s government. In 1950, he went to Vietnam on invitation and assisted Vietnam troops and civilians in their Anti-French War. In 1951, he joined the Korean War and served as vice commander of the Chinese People''s Volunteer Army. In June 1952, he came back to China by order for the sake of establishing the PLA Military Engineering Institute and he became principal and commissar of the institute. Later, he served as the PLA Deputy Chief of General Staff, Deputy Head of Commission of Science, Technology and Industry for National Defense, Vice Minister of Ministry of National Defense. In 1955, he was conferred the military rank of General. On March 16<sup>th</sup> 1961, Comrade Chengeng passed away from disease in Shanghai, aged 58.</span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 200px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align: center"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt"><img alt="" hspace="10" align="middle" vspace="10" border="0" style="width: 122px; height: 179px" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/University_Culture/image019.jpg" /></span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 511px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align: center"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">Bronze Statue of Zhenghe</span></b></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 200px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align: center"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt"><img alt="" hspace="10" align="middle" vspace="10" border="0" style="width: 110px; height: 164px" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/University_Culture/image021.jpg" /></span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 511px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">Bronze Statue of Dengshichang</span></b></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 200px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align: center"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt"><img alt="" hspace="10" align="middle" vspace="10" border="0" style="width: 118px; height: 175px" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/University_Culture/image023.jpg" /></span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 511px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal" align="left" style="margin-right: 0.9pt; text-align: left"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">Bronze Statue of </span><img height="17" alt="" width="93" align="middle" border="0" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/University_Culture/olhf1.JPG" /></b></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;</span></b></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 200px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align: center"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt"><img alt="" hspace="10" align="middle" vspace="10" border="0" style="width: 171px; height: 150px" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/University_Culture/image025.jpg" /></span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 511px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">University Spirit: </span></b><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Loyalty, Fortitude, Solidarity, Creativity</span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">In August 2003, the 50<sup>th</sup> anniversary of HEU, the conference of the Alumni Association of the Harbin Military Engineering Institute set &quot;loyalty and devotion, fortitude and striving, arduous struggle, solidarity and cooperation, truthfulness and creativity&quot; as our school spirit. Such spirit carries the essence of Harbin Military Engineering spirit and conforms to the teaching situation of our university.</span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 200px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align: center"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt"><img alt="" hspace="10" align="middle" vspace="10" border="0" style="width: 176px; height: 167px" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/University_Culture/image026.jpg" /></span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 511px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">Teaching Style: </span></b><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">Preciseness, Rigor, Strictness (being precise in academic studies, rigorous in organization, and strict in demands)</span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">Such teaching style originates from the teaching traditions of Harbin Military Engineering Institute.</span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 200px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align: center"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt"><img alt="" hspace="10" align="middle" vspace="10" border="0" style="width: 168px; height: 177px" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/University_Culture/image028.jpg" /></span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td valign="top" style="border-right: 1px solid; padding-right: 5.4pt; border-top: 1px solid; padding-left: 5.4pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: 1px solid; width: 511px; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: 1px solid">\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">Learning Style: </span></b><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">Precise and Truthful, Industrious and Creative </span></span></p>\r\n            <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 12pt">Set by principal conference of Harbin Ship Engineering Institute in 1988.</span></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</p>', NULL, 193, 1, ''),
