(52, 1, 'hrbeu', 1, 'Our Histroy', '2009-04-27 00:11:23', '2009-05-12 16:28:20', 'hrbeu', 'Our Histroy', '1953:\r\nSeptember 1, 1953: the predecessor of HEU, the PLA  Military Engineering Institute was established, and Senior General Chen Geng acted as the first president.', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">1953:</span></strong><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\nSeptember 1, 1953: the predecessor of HEU, the PLA&nbsp; Military Engineering Institute was established, and Senior General Chen Geng acted as the first president.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img alt="" style="width: 179px; height: 95px" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-87787.jpg" /></span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">1966:</span></strong><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\nApril, 1966: the Institute changed its name to Harbin Engineering Institute.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img height="114" alt="" width="384" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-29886.jpg" /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">1972:</span></strong><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\nJanuary, 1972: the Institute changed its name to Harbin Shipbuilding Engineering Institute (HSEI). </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img alt="" style="width: 143px; height: 122px" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-93211.jpg" /><img alt="" style="width: 249px; height: 127px" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/historyimg/slide0005_image018.jpg" /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">1978:</span></strong><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\nFebruary, 1978: HSEI was listed&nbsp; as one of the 88 key institutes by the State Council.<br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img alt="" style="width: 406px; height: 175px" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-32121.jpg" /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">March, 1978: seven projects hosted by HSEI won prizes in National Science Fair.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img alt="" style="width: 148px; height: 121px" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-17497.jpg" /><img alt="" style="width: 153px; height: 122px" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/historyimg/slide0007_image022.jpg" /><img alt="" style="width: 112px; height: 120px" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/historyimg/slide0007_image023.png" /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">1981:</span></strong><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\nNovember, 1981: HSEI was among the first batch of academic institutions authorized by the State Council to award master and doctoral degrees.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img alt="" style="width: 222px; height: 136px" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-10280.jpg" /><img alt="" border="0" style="width: 203px; height: 137px" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/historyimg/slide0008_image026.jpg" /><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>1985:</strong><br />\r\nApril, 1985: HSEI, among 45 academic institutions, was authorized to accept domestic visiting scholars.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img alt="" style="width: 172px; height: 125px" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/historyimg/slide0002_image007.jpg" /><img alt="" style="width: 152px; height: 124px" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/historyimg/slide0003_image013.jpg" /><img alt="" style="width: 110px; height: 124px" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/historyimg/slide0002_image009.jpg" /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">1991:</span></strong><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\nDecember, 1991: the pass rate of HEU students in the National College English Test (Band 4) was ranking the 1st in the North-east Region of China, and 9th in China. In the following years the pass rate of HEU for CET-4 was kept at the leading position.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img alt="" style="width: 319px; height: 130px" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-68667.jpg" /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">1994:</span></strong><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\nApril, 1994: HSEI was renamed as Harbin Engineering University (HEU). </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img alt="" style="width: 179px; height: 124px" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-54634.jpg" /><img alt="" border="0" style="width: 168px; height: 125px" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/historyimg/slide0010_image034.jpg" /><img alt="" style="width: 109px; height: 130px" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/historyimg/slide0002_image011.jpg" /><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">June, 1994: HEU first participated in the American 10th Mathematical Model Contest and won the first prize.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img alt="" style="width: 464px; height: 128px" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-69510.jpg" /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<font face="Times New Roman" size="2">June, 1994: the First Comprehensive and Large-Scale Deep Sea Survey of Underwater Acoustical environment in China presided by Professor Yang Shie&nbsp;of HEU achieved a success.</font></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><font face="Times New Roman" size="2"><img alt="" style="width: 241px; height: 122px" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-22623.jpg" /><img alt="" style="width: 230px; height: 122px" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/historyimg/slide0005_image019.jpg" /></font></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<span style="font-family: Arial">August, 1996: HEU was listed as a key university being enhanced by the ''211 Project'', which provides important support to Chinese 100 elite university.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img height="117" alt="" width="216" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-22244.jpg" /><img height="118" alt="" width="275" border="0" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/historyimg/slide0013_image043.jpg" /><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span>December, 1996: the Base of Electric and Electronic Education was entitled as one of the first Teaching Bases of National Science Basic Courses.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img alt="" style="width: 167px; height: 105px" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-22808.jpg" /><img alt="" border="0" style="width: 164px; height: 105px" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/historyimg/slide0014_image048.png" /><img alt="" border="0" style="width: 165px; height: 104px" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/historyimg/slide0014_image051.gif" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span><strong>1997:<br />\r\n</strong>January, 1997: the Underwater Acoustic Lab passed the national inspection.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-family: Arial"><img alt="" style="width: 302px; height: 118px" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-14273.jpg" /></span><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">November, 1997: the Measuring Ship Monitor of the Middle-and-long Distance Sea passed&nbsp; test, marking pioneering position of HEU in this area.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\nNovember, 1997: sea trial success of Swath Bathymetry Sonar, making a new era of HEU''s research in this area.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img height="114" alt="" width="223" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-81595.jpg" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span><strong>1998:<br />\r\n</strong>June, 1998: the first team of undergraduate students involved in a joint education program went to Japan.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img alt="" style="width: 236px; height: 148px" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-77462.jpg" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span><strong>1999:<br />\r\n</strong>February, 1999: HEU was formally announced to be under the administration of the Commission of Science Technology and Industry for National Defense.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<strong><span style="font-family: Arial">2000:<br />\r\n</span></strong><span style="font-family: Arial">January, 2000: Shipbuilding Technical Design Institute of HEU obtained the ISO9000 authentication, indicating&nbsp; internationalizing progress of HEU quality management on scientific products.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img alt="" style="width: 244px; height: 118px" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-39940.jpg" /><br />\r\n<span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span>July, 2000: the experiment on Intelligent Underwater Robot was undertaken successfully, which marked HEU had paced up with the world level in intelligent underwater robot technology.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img alt="" style="width: 254px; height: 136px" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-29073.jpg" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span><strong>2001:<br />\r\n</strong>June, 2001: HEU construction projects supported by the ''211 Project'' and the ''9th Five-year Plan'' passed the national inspection .</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">2002:<br />\r\n</span></strong><span style="font-family: Arial">April, 2002: Underwater Acoustic Engineering, Navigation, Guidance and Control, Design and Manufacturing of Marine Structures were confirmed as National Key Disciplines by the Ministry of Education.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img height="135" alt="" width="195" border="0" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/historyimg/slide0027_image074.jpg" /><img height="135" alt="" width="169" border="0" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/historyimg/slide0027_image078.jpg" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span>May, 2002: HEU Intelligent Underwater Robot Lab was listed as one National Key Lab.<br />\r\n<span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span>December, 2002: the Commission of Science Technology and Industry for National Defense and the People''s Government of Heilongjiang Province signed an agreement to jointly construct HEU.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img alt="" border="0" style="width: 361px; height: 154px" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/historyimg/slide0029_image084.jpg" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span><strong>2003:<br />\r\n</strong>February, 2003: Intelligent Marine Robot won the second prize of the National Technology Progress Award.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img alt="" style="width: 262px; height: 114px" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-22326.gif" /><img alt="" border="0" style="width: 233px; height: 112px" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/historyimg/slide0031_image087.gif" /><br />\r\n<span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span>May, 2003: the Graduate School of HEU was formally open.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img alt="" style="width: 262px; height: 123px" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-26318.jpg" /><br />\r\n<span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span>September, 2003: HEU celebrated its 50th Anniversary, which landmarked a new development phase of HEU.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img alt="" style="width: 267px; height: 106px" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-21454.jpg" /><br />\r\n<span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span>October, 2003: National Science Park of HEU was formally open.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img alt="" style="width: 269px; height: 126px" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-11553.jpg" /><br />\r\n<span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span>November, 2003: HEU student team was ranked the 2nd place in the China University Robocon CCTV 2003.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span><strong>2004:<br />\r\n</strong>January, 2004: Prof. Xu Yuru was selected as a member of the Chinese Academy of Engineering.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img height="156" alt="" width="120" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-66907.jpg" /><br />\r\n<span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span>April, 2004: Journal of Harbin Engineering University entered into EI Retrieve. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><img alt="" style="width: 131px; height: 142px" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-60938.jpg" /><img alt="" style="width: 129px; height: 139px" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-99904.jpg" /><img alt="" style="width: 125px; height: 134px" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-24507.jpg" /><br />\r\n<span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span>May, 2004: the Base of Electric and Electronic Education passed the national inspection.<br />\r\n<span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span>November, 2004: HEU student team won the championship in the National Challenge Cup Business Plan Competition, which was for the first time a university in Northeast-China won the championship.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">2005:<br />\r\n</span></strong><span style="font-family: Arial">January, 2005: HEU officially adopted its philosophy as Precise Engineering, Academic Excellence and Pursuit of Truth.<br />\r\n<span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span>February, 2005: The 2nd HEU Congress set the developing strategies for the future 5 to 15 years by specializing in shipping industry, ocean exploration and nuclear application, and the goals as to be an internationally renowned research-oriented university with a distinctive position.<br />\r\n<span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span>April, 2005: the first Multi-functional Comprehensive Underwater Exploring Robot was successfully developed by HEU.<br />\r\n<span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span>September, 2005: HEU student team was ranked the 3rd place in the ABU Robot Contest 2005.<br />\r\n<span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span>December, 2005: the College of Nuclear Science and Technology was established, which was the first college in China specializing research and education in nuclear science and technology.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">2006:<br />\r\n</span></strong><span style="font-family: Arial">April, 2006: University Anthem was officially adopted.<br />\r\n<span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span>April, 2006: Deepwater Engineering and Technology Center was established, which landmarked research in naval architecture and ocean engineering developing into deepwater area.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><font face="Times New Roman" size="2">Today :</font></strong></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><strong><font face="Times New Roman" size="2"><img height="134" alt="" width="151" border="0" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/historyimg/slide0034_image098.jpg" /><img alt="" border="0" style="width: 171px; height: 134px" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/historyimg/slide0034_image099.jpg" /><img height="134" alt="" width="171" border="0" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/University/historyimg/slide0034_image097.jpg" /></font></strong></p>', NULL, 222, 1, '/userfiles/image/2009/05/12/2009-05-12-24507.jpg'),
(53, 1, 'hrbeu', 1, 'Brief', '2009-04-27 00:13:57', '2009-05-13 16:40:35', 'hrbeu', 'Brief', 'Harbin (Ha''erbin), capital of Heilongjiang, China''s northernmost province, is a place of many contradictions.', '<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><font size="3"><st1:city w:st="on"><span lang="EN-US">Harbin</span></st1:city></font></span><font size="3"><st1:city w:st="on"></st1:city><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span lang="EN-US">, a charming city standing in the northernmost </span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: ''Times New Roman''"><st1:place w:st="on"><st1:placetype w:st="on"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman">province</span></st1:placetype><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"> of </span><st1:placename w:st="on"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman">China</span></st1:placename></st1:place><span style="font-family: Times New Roman">. The city is entitled to its other characteristic nicknames as the &lsquo;</span><st1:place w:st="on"><st1:placename w:st="on"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman">Ice</span></st1:placename><st1:placetype w:st="on"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman">City</span></st1:placetype></st1:place><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"> of the Northland&rsquo; and &lsquo;Oriental Paris&rsquo;. </span><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span lang="EN-US"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span lang="EN-US"><o:p></o:p></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: ''Times New Roman''"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span lang="EN-US"><font size="3">Harbin is located in the centre of Northeast Asia, which is considered a mid-temperate zone with a characteristic climate; the seasons are distinct with a short spring and a relatively short but cool summer, Harbin is perhaps most famous for its longer artic-like winter conditions.&nbsp;</font></span></span><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><font size="3"><st1:city w:st="on"><span lang="EN-US">Harbin</span></st1:city></font></span><font size="3"><st1:city w:st="on"></st1:city><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span lang="EN-US"> is also the pivot for the first Eurasia Land Bridge and Air Corridor and its prime waterway is the infamous &lsquo;</span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: ''Times New Roman''"><st1:placename w:st="on"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman">Songhua</span></st1:placename><st1:placetype w:st="on"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman">River</span></st1:placetype><span style="font-family: Times New Roman">&rsquo;, which reaches across the city and continues through into </span><st1:country-region w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman">Russia</span></st1:place></st1:country-region><span style="font-family: Times New Roman">. </span><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span lang="EN-US"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span lang="EN-US"><o:p></o:p></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: ''Times New Roman''"><o:p></o:p></span><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><font size="3"><st1:city w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on"></st1:place></st1:city></font></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><font size="3"><span lang="EN-US"><a href="javascript:dyn.onClickNextTbn()"><img id="imgb" title="下一张" src="http://travel.maptown.cn/uploadfile/2005/10/28/3/2005102816472952393.jpg" style="width: 152px; height: 196px" alt="" /></a><a href="javascript:dyn.onClickNextTbn()"><img id="imgb" title="下一张" src="http://photo.hlj.net/images/2009-01-20/1232428283672.jpg" style="width: 407px; height: 195px" alt="" /></a><a href="javascript:dyn.onClickNextTbn()"><img id="imgb" title="下一张" src="http://travel.ntonline.cn/tour/up/xwpic/200812342589829.jpg" style="width: 194px; height: 195px" alt="" /></a></span></font></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><font size="3"><st1:city w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on"><span lang="EN-US">Harbin</span></st1:place></st1:city></font></span><font size="3"><st1:city w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on"></st1:place></st1:city><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span lang="EN-US">, is an interesting city with its long history, is the cradle of Jin and Qing Dynasties and in the past and today is also a popular settlement for various ethnic minority groups. The Hans as the majority, there are still over 40 other ethnic minorities including Mans, Huis, Mongolians, Koreans and etc. </span></span></font></p>\r\n<p><font size="3"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span lang="EN-US"><a href="javascript:dyn.onClickNextTbn()"><img id="imgb" title="下一张" src="http://www.hlj.xinhuanet.com/lytd/2005-05/13/xin_42311041509354842176918.jpg" style="width: 160px; height: 161px" alt="" /></a><a href="javascript:dyn.onClickNextTbn()"><img id="imgb" title="下一张" src="http://www.hrblyj.com.cn/images/金上京历史博物馆2.JPG" style="width: 411px; height: 160px" alt="" /></a><a href="javascript:dyn.onClickNextTbn()"><img id="imgb" title="下一张" src="http://www.cycnet.com/cms/2006/2006news/08hlj/tpbd/200810/W020081010006623697095.jpg" style="width: 189px; height: 160px" alt="" /></a></span></span></font></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span lang="EN-US"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span lang="EN-US"><o:p></o:p></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: ''Times New Roman''"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span lang="EN-US"><font size="3">The history of </font></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: ''Times New Roman''"><font size="3"><st1:city w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman">Harbin</span></st1:place></st1:city><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"> can be traced back to 22,000 years, the late Paleolithic age, where the first traces of human activity were discovered. In the early 20<sup>th</sup> Century, </span><st1:city w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman">Harbin</span></st1:place></st1:city><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"> has turned into an important international trading port. With over 160,000 immigrants making home in </span><st1:city w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman">Harbin</span></st1:place></st1:city><span style="font-family: Times New Roman">, and the establishment of 16 consulates, </span></font></span><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><font size="3"><st1:city w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on"><span lang="EN-US">Harbin</span></st1:place></st1:city></font></span><font size="3"><st1:city w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on"></st1:place></st1:city><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span lang="EN-US"> has become a famous international metropolitan. </span></span></font></p>', NULL, 194, 1, ''),
(54, 1, 'hrbeu', 1, 'Local features', '2009-04-27 00:15:22', '2009-05-13 16:59:37', 'hrbeu', 'Local features', 'Also known as ''Ice City'', Harbin is most famous in China for its winter scenery and bitterly cold temperatures that accompany the freezing environment.', '<p><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-family: Arial">Harbin, </span>the capital of Heilongjiang province of People''s Republic of China, is one of the sources of ice and snow culture in the world. Geographically, it is located in Northeast China under the direct influence of the cold winter wind from Siberia. The average temperature in summer is 21.2 degrees Celsius, -16.8 degrees Celsius in winter. It can be as cold as - 38.1 degrees Celsius in winter.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">Officially, the festival starts from January 5th and it lasts one month. However often the exhibitions open earlier and last longer, weather permitting. Ice sculpture decoration ranges from the modern technology of lasers to traditional ice lanterns. There are ice lantern park touring activities held in many parks in the city. Winter activities in the festival include Yabuli alpine skiing, winter-swimming in Songhua River, and the ice-lantern exhibition in Zhaolin Garden. Snow carving and ice and snow recreations are world famous. he Harbin festival is one of the world''s four largest ice and snow festivals, along with Japan''s Sapporo Snow Festival, Canada''s Quebec City Winter Carnival, and Norway''s Ski Festival.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small">The 2007 festival featured the Canadian theme, <i>in memoriam</i> of Canadian doctor Norman Bethune. It also a Guinness Record of the largest snow sculpture: 250 metres long, 28&nbsp;feet (8.5&nbsp;m) high, using over 13,000 cubic metres of snow. The composition consisted of two parts: &quot;Niagara Falls&quot; and &quot;Crossing the Bering Strait&quot; (the latter depicting the migration of the First Nations).</span></p>\r\n<p><a href="javascript:dyn.onClickNextTbn()"><img id="imgb" title="下一张" alt="" style="width: 246px; height: 184px" src="http://i3.sinaimg.cn/ty/o/p/2007-12-24/U397P6T12D3379749F44DT20071224172938.jpg" /></a><a href="javascript:dyn.onClickNextTbn()"><img id="imgb" title="下一张" alt="" style="width: 222px; height: 184px" src="http://news.xinhuanet.com/photo/2008-12/23/xin_01212052321243900018234.jpg" /></a><a href="javascript:dyn.onClickNextTbn()"><img id="imgb" title="下一张" alt="" style="width: 224px; height: 184px" src="http://laiba.tianya.cn/laiba/images/980373/12323697860500272698/A/1/m.jpg" /></a></p>', NULL, 194, 1, ''),
(55, 1, 'hrbeu', 1, 'Climate in Harbin', '2009-04-27 00:16:31', '2009-04-27 00:16:31', 'hrbeu', 'Climate in Harbin', 'Harbin is the most northeastern and coldest provincial capital in China. The city has a long cold winter and short cool summers. Rainfall here is pretty minimal and even winters are surprisingly dry.', '<p>Harbin is the most northeastern and coldest provincial capital in China. The city has a long cold winter and short cool summers. Rainfall here is pretty minimal and even winters are surprisingly dry.</p>\r\n<p>The&nbsp; heaviest periods of rain will fall between July and August. Snow starts as early as November and the coldest month is January.</p>\r\n<p>It is possible to visit Harbin all year round (although in deepest winter make sure you are adequately prepared - it is impossible to stay outside for extended periods of time). Most people visit in Summer (July-September) for the exceptionally cool weather and in Winter (November-February) for the breathtaking Ice Lantern Festival.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<table border="1" bordercolor="#d3dcef" cellpadding="0">\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td height="25" colspan="13" align="center">\r\n            <p align="center"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">Average Temperatures in Harbin</font></b></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td height="25" align="center">\r\n            <p align="justify"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">Month</font></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td height="25" align="center">\r\n            <p align="justify"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">1</font></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td height="25" align="center">\r\n            <p align="justify"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">2</font></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td height="25" align="center">\r\n            <p align="justify"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">3</font></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td height="25" a