(61, 1, 'hrbeu', 3, 'Yang Shie', '2009-04-27 00:28:44', '2009-04-27 00:28:44', 'hrbeu', 'Yang Shie', 'Yang Shie, a distinguished academician and scientist, started his career in 1953. He was a lecturer at Harbin Military Engineering Institute (now Harbin Engineering University), and rendered distinguished services in developing the Department of Shipbuilding Engineering.', '<p>Yang Shie, a distinguished academician and scientist, started his career in 1953. He was a lecturer at Harbin Military Engineering Institute (now Harbin Engineering University), and rendered distinguished services in developing the Department of Shipbuilding Engineering.</p>\r\n<p>He has held important professional positions including member of the State Council''s Discipline Appraisal Organization, and vice board-chairman of China Acoustics Society. He is currently the head of Underwater Acoustics Research Institute of Harbin Engineering University. His involvement in major research projects is substantial and mainly relates to underwater acoustics engineering, but he has also made significant contributions in developing the marine acoustic measuring system and a batch of navy''s practical equipment leading international development. His current research interests include sound navigation system, underwater acoustical propagation, acoustical systems and devices.</p>\r\n<p>As a professor Yang Shie&nbsp; delivers a unique contribution in the development of marine acoustics in China: to help cultivate the first batch of underwater acoustics professional technical backbone for China, also supervised the development of state key laboratories in the field of underwater acoustics engineering, and is participating in the construction decision of marine acoustics in China. All of which has made Yang Shie&nbsp; an internationally acknowledged academic pioneer in the field of marine acoustics.</p>\r\n<p>Prof. Yang enjoys great prestige in the international acoustics science community. He has visited the United States, Japan and France many times for academic exchanges or to give lectures at the invitation these countries. Over the years he has obtained 10 brilliant awards, and has published 3 monographs, and over 40 papers. At present he undertakes state-funded research projects with a funding of over 2 million yuan RMB.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 165, 1, ''),
(62, 1, 'hrbeu', 3, 'Liao Zhenpeng', '2009-04-27 00:29:38', '2009-04-27 00:29:38', 'hrbeu', 'Liao Zhenpeng', 'Prof.Liao Zhenpeng, is a member of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, he plays an integral part at the university as both a professor and doctoral advisor in the College of Shipbuilding Engineering; and a senior scientist in the Institute of Engineering Mechanics of China Seismological Bureau.', '<p>Prof.Liao Zhenpeng, is a member of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, he plays an integral part at the university as both a professor and doctoral advisor in the College of Shipbuilding Engineering; and a senior scientist in the Institute of Engineering Mechanics of China Seismological Bureau.</p>\r\n<p>Prof.Liao''s research interests include: wave motion theories for engineering and earthquake engineering. In the area of wave motion, Prof. Liao has proposed a unified artificial-transmitting-theory for simulating various kinds of one-way waves, and thereby derived a simple transmitting boundary condition which can be applied to numerical simulation of waves in open and complex systems of large scale.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Prof. Liao and his co-workers have established a finite element technique for the near-field wave simulation. This numerical technique is decoupled both in time and space and thus highly efficient for solving a series of complicated problems of wave motion, such as, analysis of structure-medium dynamic interaction, scattering of complicated objects and earthquake resistant design of engineering structures of large scale. He has proved that the boundary condition in the numerical simulation is equivalent to the radiation condition at infinity in the corresponding analytical studies in the sense of that accuracy of the boundary condition can be made consistent with those of the finite elements or finite differences adopted in the numerical simulation., this boundary condition is internationally called the ''Liao''s Absorbing Boundary Condition'' and is widely cited in papers and monographs by other researchers working in various fields such as: electromagnetics, geophysics, acoustics and civil engineering. It has also been adopted in lecture materials for graduate students in the related disciplines based on the transmitting theory at famous universities.</p>\r\n<p>Email: <a href="mailto:liaozhenpeng@hrbeu.edu.cn">liaozhenpeng@hrbeu.edu.cn</a></p>', NULL, 133, 1, ''),
(63, 1, 'hrbeu', 3, 'Xu Yuru', '2009-04-27 00:30:19', '2009-04-27 00:30:19', 'hrbeu', 'Xu Yuru', 'Major Achievements: Prof. Xu Yuru is the subject leader of Naval Architecture and Ocean Engineering, the national key discipline of Harbin Engineering University. For more than 30 years, he managed and completed various and numerous engineering research projects here at the university.', '<p>Name: Xu Yuru</p>\r\n<p>Field: Submarine design</p>\r\n<p>Work location: Harbin Engineering University, 145 Nantong street, Harbin, China</p>\r\n<p>Academic division: Mechanical and Vehicle Engineering</p>\r\n<p>Year of election: 2003</p>\r\n<p>Major Achievements: Prof. Xu Yuru is the subject leader of Naval Architecture and Ocean Engineering, the national key discipline of Harbin Engineering University. For more than 30 years, he managed and completed various and numerous engineering research projects here at the university. These projects have focused especially on the fast developing technology of autonomous underwater vehicles of China. He has made important contributions to the system simulation, intelligent control architecture, system integration and so forth in his field of expertise.</p>\r\n<p>In respect of submersible maneuverability and dynamic positioning system, He has obtained many research achievements. As a manager of his research group, he and his fellows realized the submersible dynamic positioning system with four degrees of freedom successfully in 1990. This is the foundation and milestone of dynamic positioning technology of China. He made great contributions in the key technology of submersible system modeling and dynamic simulation.</p>\r\n<p>Email: <a href="mailto:xuyuru@hrbeu.edu.cn">xuyuru@hrbeu.edu.cn</a></p>', NULL, 125, 1, ''),
(64, 1, 'hrbeu', 3, 'Wang Zhongqi', '2009-04-27 00:30:56', '2009-04-27 00:30:56', 'hrbeu', 'Wang Zhongqi', 'Prof.Wang Zhongqi, a member of Chinese Academy of Engineering, expert of thermal impeller machinery, after graduation from Harbin Institute of Technology, he took a teaching post there.', '<p>Prof.Wang Zhongqi, a member of Chinese Academy of Engineering, expert of thermal impeller machinery, after graduation from Harbin Institute of Technology, he took a teaching post there. In 1985, he was promoted as a professor. In 1986 he began to act as a doctoral supervisor and was elected to Chinese Academy of Engineering in 1998. He had been awarded the title of ''Excellent Teacher'' and ''Model Worker'' in national system of education. Currently, he is the deputy chair of Heat Engine Aerothermodynamics SIC of Chinese Society of Engineering Thermal-physics, the Director of Heilongjiang Society of Mechanics, and the deputy director-general of Harbin Society of Engineering Thermal-physics.</p>\r\n<p>In nearly 40 years, Prof. Wang Zhongqi published more than 120 papers on many international academic periodicals, composed 3 monographs, including ''Theory of Turbomachinery'' and ''The Three-dimensional Flow Computation of Turbomachinery and it''s Basics of Math and Gas Dynamics'', nearly 2,000,000 words. His works were cited 70 times by colleagues both at home and abroad, some of his papers were translated in full text by the US or published on American AD Reports. In 1993, Prof. Wang Zhongqi was awarded the 2nd Prize of National Natural Science.</p>\r\n<p>Email: <a href="mailto:wangzhongqi@hrbeu.edu.cn">wangzhongqi@hrbeu.edu.cn</a></p>', NULL, 133, 1, ''),
(65, 1, 'hrbeu', 3, 'Gao Yuchen', '2009-04-27 00:31:34', '2009-04-27 00:31:34', 'hrbeu', 'Gao Yuchen', 'Academician Gao Yuchen (deceased in 2006), doctoral advisor, expert on solid mechanics, and professor at Harbin Engineering University, was elected to the Chinese Academy of Science in 2001.', '<p>Academician Gao Yuchen (deceased in 2006), doctoral advisor, expert on solid mechanics, and professor at Harbin Engineering University, was elected to the Chinese Academy of Science in 2001. He received his BSc degree from the Mathematic Department of Peking University in 1960, and later received his MSc degree from the Mechanical Department of Tsinghua University in 1966. His main research includes: crack-tip, microscopic mechanics of composites and nonlinear continuum mechanics. In the crack-tip field, he gained a series of singular solutions of a quasi-static growing crack in perfect plasticity and power-hardening plastic materials. He also found that the singularity of plane strain plasticity field of dynamic propagating crack is accompanied by shock wave. On microscopic mechanics of composites, he established a bridging model of fibre composite material and the interface fatigue wear model.</p>\r\n<p>On nonlinear continuum mechanics, he proposed the constitutive relationship between two large spring deformations and accomplished the analysis of stress tensor under large deformations, which solved many problems on singular points of large deformation.</p>', NULL, 116, 1, ''),
(66, 1, 'hrbeu', 3, 'Sun Yufa', '2009-04-27 00:32:05', '2009-04-27 00:32:05', 'hrbeu', 'Sun Yufa', 'Prof. Sun Yufa, is a member of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, and honorary dean of the College of Nuclear Science and Technology.', '<p>Prof. Sun Yufa, is a member of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, and honorary dean of the College of Nuclear Science and Technology.</p>\r\n<p>Email: <a href="mailto:sunyufa@hrbeu.edu.cn">sunyufa@hrbeu.edu.cn</a> <br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 113, 1, ''),
(67, 1, 'hrbeu', 3, 'Wen Xueyou', '2009-04-27 00:32:33', '2009-04-27 00:32:33', 'hrbeu', 'Wen Xueyou', 'Prof. Wen Xueyou, is a member of the Chinese Academy of Engineering.', '<p>Prof. Wen Xueyou, is a member of the Chinese Academy of Engineering.</p>\r\n<p>Email: <a href="mailto:wenxueyou@hrbeu.edu.cn">wenxueyou@hrbeu.edu.cn</a> <br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 122, 1, ''),
(68, 1, 'hrbeu', 13, 'College Introduction', '2009-04-29 06:10:12', '2009-04-29 06:10:12', 'hrbeu', 'College Introduction', 'The College of Civil Engineering includes 5 regular undergraduate programs. They are Civil Engineering, Building Environment and Equipment Engineering, Water Supply and Sewerage Engineering, Engineering Mechanics, and Flight Vehicle Design and Engineering. ', '<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>Introduction</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">The College of Civil Engineering includes 5 regular undergraduate programs. They are Civil Engineering, Building Environment and Equipment Engineering, Water Supply and Sewerage Engineering, Engineering Mechanics, and Flight Vehicle Design and Engineering. The College confers master''s degrees in Solid Mechanics, Structural Engineering, Thermal Power Engineering, Aerospace Propulsion Theory and Engineering, General and Fundamental Mechanics, Engineering Mechanics, Flight Vehicle Design, Engineering Thermophysics, Disaster Prevention and Reduction Engineering and Protective Engineering, and Man-Machine and Environmental Engineering. Furthermore, doctoral degrees are conferred in Solid Mechanics, General and Fundamental Mechanics, and Engineering Mechanics. Particularly, Solid Mechanics and Aerospace Engineering are respectively the key disciplines in the Commission of Science Technology and Industry for National Defense and Heilongjiang province. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">The College is committed to generating, disseminating, and preserving knowledge, and to working with others to bring this knowledge back to the country and the society. The College is dedicated to providing her students with an education that combines rigorous academic study and the excitement of discovery with the support and intellectual stimulation of a diverse campus community. The College does her best to develop in each member of the College community the ability and passion to work wisely, creatively, and effectively.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>History</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">HEU''s predecessor, Harbin Institute of Military Engineering, was China'' most famous and important military institute. The present Civil Engineering College was formed when the specifically military elements of the department were removed. The term of ''second department'' which remained admitted its first undergraduates in 1972, graduated students in 1981, and doctoral students in 1986. The specific sign of ''second department'' has undergone numerous changes to articulate her development and emphasis. From Department of Missile Engineering, to Department of Civil Engineering, to College of Civil Engineering as well as Department of Aerospace Engineering, the College (department) has been contributing much to the national defense and welfare.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>Our Alumni </strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">In the past thirty years, more than 4,000 students obtained bachelor degree, master degree and PhD. Many of them serve in the field of national defense, shipbuilding and civil engineering, respectively. Some have become principals in their areas of specialties. Hundreds of our graduates have become professors or otherwise considered experts. Especially, one of our alumni is now the youngest alternate member of The Communist Party Central Committee of China.</span></p>', NULL, 177, 1, ''),
(69, 1, 'hrbeu', 13, 'Programs Offered', '2009-04-29 06:13:48', '2009-04-29 06:13:48', 'hrbeu', 'Programs Offered', '   Bachelor in Aerocraft Propusion Engineering\r\n   Bachelor in Building Environment and Equipment Engineering \r\n   Bachelor in Civil Engineering \r\n   Bachelor in Engineering Mechanics \r\n   Bachelor in Flight Vehicle Design and Engineering \r\n   Bachelor in Water Supply and Sewerage Engineering ', '<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">Undergraduate Programs&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></strong><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Aerocraft Propusion Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Building Environment and Equipment Engineering <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Civil Engineering <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Engineering Mechanics <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Flight Vehicle Design and Engineering <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Water Supply and Sewerage Engineering </span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">Postgraduate Programs&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span></strong><span style="font-family: Arial">&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Aeronautical &amp; Astronautical Propulsion Theory &amp; Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Disaster Prevention and Reduction Engineering and Protective Engineering <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Engineering Mechanics<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Engineering Thermophysics<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in General and Fundamental Mechanics <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Man-Machine and Environmental Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Manufacturing Engineering of Aerospace Vehicle<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Master in Aerospace Propulsion Theory and Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Solid Mechanics<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Structural Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Thermal Power Engineering</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">PhD Research Fields&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></strong><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Ph.D in Engineering Mechanics<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Ph.D in General and Fundamental Mechanics<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Ph.D in Solid Mechanics</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">Postdordorate R&amp;D Bases&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></strong><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Postdoctoral R&amp;D Base in Mechanics</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">Professional Master of Engineering Programs&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></strong><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Professional Master of Engineering in Aerospace Engineering <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Professional Master of Engineering in Architectural and Civil Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Professional Master of Engineering in Mechanical Engineering</span></p>', NULL, 224, 1, ''),
(70, 1, 'hrbeu', 13, 'Staff', '2009-04-29 06:14:32', '2009-04-29 06:14:32', 'hrbeu', 'Staff', 'With strong strength of the teaching staff, we have 101 staff, 19 of which are professors (including 9 doctoral supervisors), 23 of which are associate professors.', '<p><span style="font-family: Arial">With strong strength of the teaching staff, we have 101 staff, 19 of which are professors (including 9 doctoral supervisors), 23 of which are associate professors. The faculty of this College have already published more than 500 journal''s and conference''s papers and 20 books home and abroad, more than 60 of which have had significant influence on national and international scientific community.</span></p>', NULL, 149, 1, ''),
(71, 1, 'hrbeu', 13, 'Research', '2009-04-29 06:15:43', '2009-04-29 06:15:43', 'hrbeu', 'Research', 'The College''s commitment to combining education with the creation of knowledge provides a fertile environment for research that has spawned a host of scientific breakthroughs and technical advances.', '<p>The College''s commitment to combining education with the creation of knowledge provides a fertile environment for research that has spawned a host of scientific breakthroughs and technical advances. Achievements since 2000 include undertaking the projects of the National Science Fund, Doctoral Fund of National Education Ministry and fund of the province and ministry, as well as some other military and civil projects, many of which are awarded by the province, the ministry and the nation.</p>', NULL, 122, 1, ''),
