(78, 1, 'hrbeu', 26, 'College Introduction', '2009-04-29 06:23:59', '2009-04-29 06:31:38', 'hrbeu', 'College Introduction', 'The College of Nuclear Science and Technology was founded in 2005.', '<p><span style="font-family: Arial">The College of Nuclear Science and Technology was founded in 2005. In 1959, Harbin Institute of Military Engineering established Nuclear Power Equipment Department, which later developed into Nuclear Engineering and Technology College. After many years'' development and self-enhancement, the College distinguished itself with the honor of having a key discipline of Ministry level. Now the College has been authorized to confer PhD degree in Nuclear Power Science and Engineering, and master degrees in Nuclear Energy Science and Engineering, Radiation and Environmental Protection, Nuclear Fuel Environment and Material, and Nuclear Technology and Applications. Its research fields cover nuclear power equipment performance, nuclear power equipment safety and reliability, nuclear power equipment operation and simulation, nuclear power equipment control and observation, nuclear power equipment thermal hydraulics, and nuclear power equipment and device. The faculty is a highly responsible, dedicated, conscientious team with great academic achievements. More than twenty teachers have oversee experiences for training, research or degree pursuing. The College has been in close contact with schools and research centers both at home and abroad. So far, the College has cultivated over 1,000 graduates with bachelor degrees.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">The College has a very strong academic background. During the period from the ''7th Five-year Plan'' to the ''9th Five-year Plan'', the College has undertaken more than 50 relative research projects and been awarded with over 30 Progress Awards in invention and technology either of ministry level or national level. In the recent 5 years, the faculty has published around 100 academic papers and undertaken 42 research projects such as nuclear energy exploitation, nuclear power comprehensive simulation and design technology. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">In accordance with the demands of national higher education reform, the College is undergoing reforms to combine current and modern teaching methods with innovative mechanism. During the ''11th Five-year Plan'' period, the University will spare no effort to make the college a national base for cultivating high-quality talents for the nuclear technology industry. In the near future, the College is striving to reach the goal of becoming an international institute.</span></p>', NULL, 118, 1, ''),
(79, 1, 'hrbeu', 26, 'Programs Offered', '2009-04-29 06:25:19', '2009-04-29 06:31:49', 'hrbeu', 'Programs Offered', 'Bachelor in Nuclear Energy Engineering and Technology', '<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>Undergraduate Programs&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Nuclear Energy Engineering and Technology </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>Postgraduate Programs&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Nuclear Energy Science and Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Nuclear Fuel Environment and Material<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Nuclear Technology and Applications<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Radiation and Environmental Protection</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>PhD Research Fields&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Ph.D in Nuclear Power Science and Engineering</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>Professional Master of Engineering Programs&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Professional Master of Engineering in Nuclear Energy and Nuclear Technology</span></p>', NULL, 129, 1, ''),
(80, 1, 'hrbeu', 26, 'Staff', '2009-04-29 06:26:06', '2009-04-29 06:32:03', 'hrbeu', 'Staff', 'The College of Nuclear Science and Technology has a group of teaching staff who are extremely hard working with highly qualified abilities and owns a very strong team of teaching staff .', '<p>The College of Nuclear Science and Technology has a group of teaching staff who are extremely hard working with highly qualified abilities and owns a very strong team of teaching staff . Now the College has 42 academic and 10 administrative staff, among which 12 are professors including 6 doctoral advisers, over 3 are associate professors. The faculty have pretty strong academic profiles. 22 faculty members are with master degrees which is 42% of the whole faculty, and 16 with doctor degrees, 31% of the faculty. The College is young and energetic with about 64% members are under the age of 35. Over 20 teachers have received long-term overseas training, or involved in the annual international short-term programs supported by the College or the University. Many of our academic staff enjoy high reputation and are members and organizers of national or international academic organizations.</p>', NULL, 124, 1, '');
