(83, 1, 'hrbeu', 15, 'College Introduction', '2009-04-29 06:33:44', '2009-04-29 06:33:44', 'hrbeu', 'College Introduction', 'The history of the Automation College can be traced back to 1953, when Harbin PLA Military Engineering Institute was founded.', '<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>Brief : </strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">The history of the Automation College can be traced back to 1953, when Harbin PLA Military Engineering Institute was founded. The College is being developed and strengthened through its core disciplines of ''Ocean Tunnel Measuring'' and ''Ship-Electricity''. The College is one of the teaching and research backbones of HEU. There are 6 undergraduate programs including Automation, Measuring and Control Technology and Instruments, Electrical Engineering and its Automation, Detection Guidance and Control Technology, Biomedical Engineering, and Aviation Technology; 16 master programs including Control Theory and Control Engineering, Navigation, Guidance and Control, Pattern Recognition and Intelligent Systems, Detection Technology and Automatic Equipment, Electric Machines and Electric Apparatus, Power System and its Automation, Precision Instrument and Machinery, Biomedical Engineering, Mechantronic Engineering, Systems Engineering, System Analysis and Integration, High Voltage and Insulation Technology, Power System and its Automation, Power Electronics and Power Drives, Traffic Information Engineering &amp; Control, and Detection and Measuring Technology and Instrument; 6 doctoral programs including Control Theory and Control Engineering, Navigation, Guidance and Control, Precision Instrument and Machinery, Detection Technology and Automation Equipment, Pattern Recognition and Intelligent Systems, and System Engineering. In addition, the nationally top ranking discipline of Control Science and Engineering has a Postdoctoral R&amp;D Base. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">The students of the College also receive many benefits set up by the College, including scholarships and sustentation fund for students who are in short of funds. There are about 40 percent of College students continue to pursue their master degrees every year. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>Courses :</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">The Automation College is one of the teaching and research backbones of HEU. There are 6 bachelor programs including Automation, Measuring and Control Technology and Instruments, Electrical Engineering and its Automation, Detection, Guidance and Control Technology, Biomedical Engineering, and Aviation Technology; 16 master programs including Control Theory and Control Engineering, Navigation, Guidance and Control, Pattern Recognition and Intelligent Systems, Measuring and Testing Technologies and Instruments, Power Electronics and Power Drives, Power System and its Automation, Precision Instrument and Machinery, Biomedical Engineering, Mechantronic Engineering, System Analysis and Integration, Electric Machines and Electric Apparatus, Detection Technology and Automatic Equipments, Traffic Information Engineering &amp; Control, High Voltage and Insulation Technology, Theory and New Technology of Electrical Engineering and Systems Engineering; 6 doctoral programs including Control Theory and Control Engineering, Navigation, Guidance and Control, Precision Instrument and Machinery, Detection Technology and Automation Equipment, Pattern Recognition and Intelligent Systems and Systems Engineering. In addition, the first ranked discipline of Control Science and Engineering has the postdoctoral research station. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">In 2001, the discipline of Navigation, Guidance and Control was appraised as a national key discipline. During the process of prejudication and proposal of the National 10th Five-years Plan and the ''211 Project'', Control Theory and Control Engineering and Navigation, Guidance and Control are listed as the key disciplines. To be internationally leading, the College has invested&nbsp; 23 million yuan RMB for the two disciplines'' further construction.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>Our experience:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">The College has cultivated more than 3,600 bachelors and 530 doctors and masters. Now the majority of the graduates are the backbones in the fields of national economic and defense industry, scientific research and higher education. Currently there are 1,972 undergraduates, 450 master candidates, 150 doctors candidates and 11 post-doctoral researchers at the College.<br />\r\n</span></p>', NULL, 159, 1, ''),
(84, 1, 'hrbeu', 15, 'Programs Offered', '2009-04-29 06:35:08', '2009-04-29 06:35:08', 'hrbeu', 'Programs Offered', 'Undergraduate Programs     \r\nBachelor in Automation \r\nBachelor in Aviation Technology ', '<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>Undergraduate Programs&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Automation <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Aviation Technology <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Biomedical Engineering <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Detection, Guidance and Control Technology <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Electrical Engineering and its Automation <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Measuring and Control Technology and Instruments </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>Postgraduate Programs&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Biomedical Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Control Theory and Control Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Detection Technology and Automatic Equipment<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Electric Machines and Electric Apparatus<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in High Voltage and Insulation Technology<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Measuring and Testing Technologies and Instruments<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Mechatronic Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Navigation, Guidance and Control<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Pattern Recognition and Intelligent Systems<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Power Electronics and Power Drives<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Power System and its Automation<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Precision Instrument and Machinery<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in System Analysis and Integration<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Systems Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Theory and New Technology of Electrical Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Traffic Information Engineering &amp; Control</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>PhD Research Fields&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Ph.D in Control Theory and Control Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Ph.D in Detection Technology and Automatic Equipment<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Ph.D in Navigation, Guidance and Control<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Ph.D in Pattern Recognition and Intelligent Systems<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Ph.D in Precision Instrument and Machinery<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Ph.D in Systems Engineering</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>Postdordorate R&amp;D Bases&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Postdoctoral R&amp;D Base in Control Science and Engineering</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>Professional Master of Engineering Programs&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Professional Master of Engineering in Control Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Professional Master of Engineering in Electrical Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Professional Master of Engineering in Instrument and Meter Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Professional Master of Engineering in Project Management</span></p>', NULL, 179, 1, ''),
(85, 1, 'hrbeu', 15, 'Staff', '2009-04-29 06:36:29', '2009-04-29 06:36:29', 'hrbeu', 'Staff', 'The College has 175 staff among which 48 are professors or senior research fellows including 29 doctoral advisers', '<p><span style="font-family: Arial">The College has 175 staff among which 48 are professors or senior research fellows including 29 doctoral advisers, 39 are associate professors or senior engineers. About 40 percent of the faculty has overseas study or research experiences in the USA, Germany, the UK, Sweden and Japan, and so on.</span></p>', NULL, 128, 1, ''),
(86, 1, 'hrbeu', 15, 'Research', '2009-04-29 06:37:15', '2009-04-29 06:37:15', 'hrbeu', 'Research', 'The College has pretty strong strength and distinct characteristics of scientific research.', '<p>The College has pretty strong strength and distinct characteristics of scientific research. In recent years, the College has been awarded with 12 national-level technological prizes and more than 50 provincial and ministerial prizes. The technologies of ship stabilization and microcomputer inertial guidance have reached the advanced level in the world and top-level in the country. More than 600 papers have been published on domestic and foreign academic publications and proceedings among which over 70 were published on international academic publications and proceedings, and more than 250 were published on national academic publications. Additionally, more than 50 monographs of the faculty members have been printed.</p>', NULL, 113, 1, ''),
