(88, 1, 'hrbeu', 16, 'College Introduction', '2009-04-29 17:51:36', '2009-04-29 17:51:36', 'hrbeu', 'College Introduction', 'Welcome to the College of Underwater Acoustic Engineering. On this site you can learn about our graduate and undergraduate degree programs. ', '<p>Welcome to the College of Underwater Acoustic Engineering. On this site you can learn about our graduate and undergraduate degree programs. You will also learn about the wide variety of ongoing research activities within the College.<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n<strong>What''s underwater acoustic engineering?</strong></p>\r\n<p>What is the province of underwater acoustic engineering research? The underwater acoustic engineering means to use sound wave to survey, locate, navigate, recognize and communicate in seawater (water). It is an engineering subject which integrates physics, electronic technology, information engineering, computer technology, sensor technology and is widely applied to national defense and national (omitted) economic construction. Sound wave is the most effective carrier for transmitting information in seawater (water). With the arrival of the 21st century,&nbsp; more emphasis will be put on the development of ocean, underwater acoustic engineering technology, which is considered as one of the leading technologies in the field of ocean development, and is likely to witness with greater challenges and more opportunities.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Introduction:</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nThere are 2 undergraduate programs including Electronic and Information Engineering (Underwater Acoustics) and Electronic and Information Science and Technology; there are 7 master programs including Underwater Acoustics Engineering, Acoustics, Signal and Information Processing, Communication and Information Systems, Environmental Engineering, Weapon Systems and Utilization Engineering, and Detection, Measuring and Testing Technologies and Instruments; there are 3 doctoral programs including Underwater Acoustic Engineering, Signal and Information Processing, and Communication and Information&nbsp; Systems. In addition, Naval Architecture and Ocean Engineering has a Postdoctoral R&amp;D Base. As the earliest teaching and scientific research department in the field of underwater acoustic engineering, the College has the unique national key discipline of underwater acoustic engineering, and has the first batch of doctoral programs and Postdoctoral R&amp;D Base in China. The unique National Key Laboratory of Underwater Acoustic Technology was established here.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Facilities:</strong></p>\r\n<p>The College owns a huge variety of technically advanced facilities and labs for teaching and scientific research. The National Key Laboratory of Underwater Acoustic Technology has several subsections, such as Center of Underwater Acoustic Information Processing, Sonar System Environmental Lab, Underwater Acoustic Signal Channel Simulating Lab and Gravitational Low Noise Water Tunnel Lab. There are 15 workstations and several hundreds of personal computers in the labs. At the same time, labs are equipped with large numbers of advanced software tools, such as computing software for sound field and vibration, special software for signal processing and modern electronic design automatic software (MATLAB, DATAVIEW, DADISP, ANSYS, IDL, EDA, SYSNOISE, etc). Additionally, the teaching Lab for Underwater Acoustic is equipped with advanced measuring instruments and apparatus.</p>', NULL, 142, 1, ''),
(89, 1, 'hrbeu', 16, 'Programs Offered', '2009-04-29 17:52:40', '2009-04-29 17:52:40', 'hrbeu', 'Programs Offered', 'Undergraduate Programs     \r\nBachelor in Electronic and Information Engineering (Underwater Acoustics)\r\nBachelor in Electronic and Information Science and Technology ', '<p><strong>Undergraduate Programs&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Electronic and Information Engineering (Underwater Acoustics)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Electronic and Information Science and Technology</p>\r\n<p><strong>Postgraduate Programs&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Acoustics<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Communication and Information Systems<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Environmental Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Measuring and Testing Technologies and Instruments<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Signal and Information Processing<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Underwater Acoustic Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Weapon Systems and Utilization Engineering</p>\r\n<p><strong>PhD Research Fields&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; Ph.D in Communication and Information Systems<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Ph.D in Signal and Information Processing<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Ph.D in Underwater Acoustic Engineering</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Postdordorate R&amp;D Bases&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Postdoctoral R&amp;D Base in Naval Architecture and Ocean Engineering</p>\r\n<p><strong>Professional Master of Engineering Programs&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; Professional Master of Engineering in Electronics and Communication Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Professional Master of Engineering in Naval Architecture and Ocean Engineering</p>', NULL, 130, 1, ''),
(90, 1, 'hrbeu', 16, 'Staff', '2009-04-29 17:53:23', '2009-04-29 17:53:23', 'hrbeu', 'Staff', 'There are 88 staff among which 26 are professors including 15 doctoral advisors and 1 specially appointed professor, 28 are associate professors. ', '<p><span lang="EN-US"><font face="Times New Roman">There are 88 staff among which 26 are professors including 15 doctoral advisors and 1 specially appointed professor, 28 are associate professors. Now many young teachers are pursuing further study abroad. The College employs various professors who are holding high regard in each of their scientific fields. Professor Yang Shie, an internationally well-known expert of underwater acoustics, is the academician of Chinese Academy of Engineering as well as the deputy chairman of the Association of China Acoustics. Professor Li Qi, an expert of underwater acoustic, is the deputy of the Association of China Acoustics as well as the chairman of the Acoustics Association of Heilongjiang Province.</font></span></p>', NULL, 115, 1, ''),
(91, 1, 'hrbeu', 16, 'Research', '2009-04-29 17:53:58', '2009-04-29 17:53:58', 'hrbeu', 'Research', 'The College has undertaken a significant amount of national mandatory scientific research projects on the base of its technological strength.', '<p><span style="font-family: Arial">The College has undertaken a significant amount of national mandatory scientific research projects on the base of its technological strength. Since 1993, great research achievements have been made. We have won&nbsp; National Scientific and Technological Progress Award. There have also been nearly a hundred awards for provincial or ministry scientific and technological progress. Since the year of 2004, the average annual research income of scientific research has more than 30 million yuan RMB.</span></p>', NULL, 104, 1, ''),
