(103, 1, 'hrbeu', 19, 'College Introduction', '2009-04-29 18:56:19', '2009-04-29 18:56:19', 'hrbeu', 'College Introduction', 'The College of Information and Communication Engineering offers academic programs leading to the following degrees:', '<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">Introduction</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">The College of Information and Communication Engineering offers academic programs leading to the following degrees:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">Undergraduate programs:&nbsp; Electronic and Information Engineering, Communication Engineering, Information Countermeasure Technology, and Microelectronics</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">Graduate programs</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">Master of Science: Communication and Information Systems, Optical Engineering, Electromagnetic Field and Microwave Technology</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">Master of Electrical Engineering: Signal and Information Processing, Circuits and Systems </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">PhD programs: Communication and Information Systems, Signal and Information Processing</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">Postdoctoral R&amp;D Base: Information and Communication Engineering.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">International cooperation</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">The College has supported more than 20&nbsp; faculty members to be trained abroad or join international research cooperation in the United States, Canada, Belgium, Britain, Japan, Australia and Germany. Over 10 members have presented their research achievements on the international conferences around the world. Meanwhile, many foreign experts from Switzerland, Japan, Belgium and Germany, have been invited to give presentations in the areas of nonlinear theory, computer graphics, digital signal processing, communication technology and experimental technology.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n</span><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">Innovation oriented</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">The sense of innovation is always the emphasis in our education. We encourage our students for all-around development and foster their abilities for innovation and practice. The students are supported to compete in National Undergraduate Electronic Design Contest and National Technological Contest for College Student. Remarkable achievements have been taken by the students include prize for National Undergraduate Electronic Design and the prize for National Technological Contest for College Student.</span></p>', NULL, 182, 1, ''),
(104, 1, 'hrbeu', 19, 'Programs Offered', '2009-04-29 18:57:35', '2009-04-29 18:57:35', 'hrbeu', 'Programs Offered', 'Undergraduate Programs\r\nBachelor in Communication Engineering\r\nBachelor in Electronic and Information Engineering', '<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>Undergraduate Programs</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Communication Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Electronic and Information Engineering <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Infomation Countermeasure Technology <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Microelectronics </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>Postgraduate Programs</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Circuit and Systems<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Communication and Information Systems<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Electromagnetic Field and Microwave Technology<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Optical Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Signal and Information Processing</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>PhD Research Fields</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Ph.D in Communication and Information Systems<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Ph.D in Signal and Information Processing</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>Postdordorate R&amp;D Bases</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Postdoctoral R&amp;D Base in Information and Communication Engineering</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>Professional Master of Engineering Programs</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Professional Master of Engineering in Electrical and Communication Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Professional Master of Engineering in Instrument and Meter Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Professional Master of Engineering in Optical Engineering</span></p>', NULL, 177, 1, ''),
(105, 1, 'hrbeu', 19, 'Staff', '2009-04-29 18:58:02', '2009-04-29 18:58:02', 'hrbeu', 'Staff', 'The College has great strength in HR and teaching resources.', '<p>The College has great strength in HR and teaching resources. There are 132 staff among which 5 are Young and Middle Aged Experts with Outstanding Contributions of national, provincial and ministerial levels, over 60 are professors including 9 doctoral advisors, 9 are associate professors, 31 lectures and experiment tutors.</p>', NULL, 132, 1, ''),
(106, 1, 'hrbeu', 19, 'Research', '2009-04-29 18:58:37', '2009-04-29 18:58:37', 'hrbeu', 'Research', 'In 1996, the College was approved to be one of eight centers of national electric and electronic education by the Ministry of Education of China.', '<p><span style="font-family: Arial">In 1996, the College was approved to be one of eight centers of national electric and electronic education by the Ministry of Education of China. The center has advanced experimental facilities for teaching the state-of-the-art electric and electronic technology. Our center is spacious to contain more than 400 students at one time and offer many other technological innovative activities for them. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">The College is also home to many research labs, such as, Signal Processing and Comprehension Lab, Communication Technology Lab, Optical Fiber Lab, Electronic Engineering Lab and Applied electronic Lab. They supply good conditions for students'' course experiments, thesis work, and especially, our faculties'' researches.</span></p>', NULL, 106, 1, ''),
