(108, 1, 'hrbeu', 20, 'College Introduction', '2009-04-29 19:01:58', '2009-04-29 19:01:58', 'hrbeu', 'College Introduction', 'The School of Economics and Management has more than 80 academic and administrative staff,', '<p><strong>Introduction:</strong></p>\r\n<p>The School of Economics and Management has more than 80 academic and administrative staff, among whom there are more than 40 professors and associate professors. The overwhelming majority has a doctor or master''s degree. There is a communication center for post-doctoral studies on management science and engineering. The School has the right to grant the doctor''s degree on Management Science and Engineering, and to grant the master''s degrees on Management Science and Engineering, Industrial Economics, Finance, Corporate Management, Technology Economy and Management, Business Administration and so on. The bachelor programs are Economics, Business Administration, International Economics and Trade, Finance, Public Finance, Public Affairs Management, and Electronic Commerce. There are more than 2,000 students at all levels in the College.</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>A training center:</strong></p>\r\n<p>To meet the demands of the new economy development era in China, the School began to offer training programs for administrative staff and officers of the government, and from enterprises. There are over 4,000 graduates from diversified training programs.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Partners:</strong></p>\r\n<p>The School has established co-operative relationship with the Business Institute of Washington University, the Business Institute of he Baltimore University and New England University of Australia, and thus created the better condition benefiting its staff and the students.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 112, 1, ''),
(109, 1, 'hrbeu', 20, 'Programs Offered', '2009-04-29 19:03:50', '2009-04-29 19:03:50', 'hrbeu', 'Programs Offered', 'Undergraduate Programs     \r\nBachelor in Business Administration \r\nBachelor in Economics', '<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>Undergraduate Programs&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Business Administration <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Economics <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Electronic Commerce <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Finance <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in International Economics and Trade <br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Public Affairs Management<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor in Public Finance</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>Postgraduate Programs&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Corporate Management (including Financial Management, Marketing, and Human Resources Management)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Accounting<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Educational Economy and Management<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Finance (including Insurance)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Industrial Economics<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in International Economics<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in International Trade<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Labor Economics<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Management Science &amp; Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in National Economics<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Political Economy<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Public Finance (including Taxation)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Quantitative Economics<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Regional Economics<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Statistics<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Technology Economy and Management<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master in Tourist Management<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Master of Business Administration</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>PhD Research Fields&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Ph.D in Management Science and Engineering</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>Postdordorate R&amp;D Bases&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Postdoctoral R&amp;D Base in Management Science and Engineering</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>Professional Master of Engineering Programs&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Professional Master of Engineering in Industrial Engineering<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; Professional Master of Engineering in Project Management</span></p>', NULL, 135, 1, ''),
(110, 1, 'hrbeu', 20, 'Staff', '2009-04-29 19:04:41', '2009-04-29 19:04:41', 'hrbeu', 'Staff', 'The School has 95 academic and administrative staff, among whom there are more than 19 professors (including 9 doctoral advisors) and 25 associate professors.', '<p><span style="font-family: Arial">The School has 95 academic and administrative staff, among whom there are more than 19 professors (including 9 doctoral advisors) and 25 associate professors. The overwhelming majority has a doctor or master''s degree. There is a communication center for post-doctoral studies on Management Science and Engineering.</span></p>', NULL, 97, 1, ''),
(111, 1, 'hrbeu', 20, 'Research', '2009-04-29 19:05:16', '2009-04-29 19:05:16', 'hrbeu', 'Research', 'The scientific research achievement of the School is remarkable.', '<p><span style="font-family: Arial">The scientific research achievement of the School is remarkable. In recent years, we have finished over 30 scientific research projects at provincial and ministerial levels, have been awarded with over 20 prizes of Science and Technology Progress at provincial and ministerial levels, have published over 60 monographs and textbooks, and over 500 academic papers. The School has experimental centers, MBA laboratories, accounting and financial laboratories, and doctor''s computer labs. Besides there are modernized information data centers, MBA''s reference rooms, complete multimedia classrooms and MBA ''s case analysis rooms and case discussion rooms. All of these have much facilitated teaching and scientific research.</span></p>', NULL, 99, 1, ''),
