(149, 1, 'hrbeu', 3, 'Job Application', '2009-04-29 23:28:44', '2009-04-29 23:28:44', 'hrbeu', 'Job Application', 'Supplying a Personal Resume and Other Relevant Documents. A  resume and any other relevant documents (in English) should be submitted with the application.', '<p><span style="font-family: Arial">Supplying a Personal Resume and Other Relevant Documents. A&nbsp; resume and any other relevant documents (in English) should be submitted with the application.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>The resume should contain the following information:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">&nbsp; Name, sex, nationality, date and place of birth, present address and occupation;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">&nbsp; Academic record of secondary education (secondary school, university or college, research institute. Include: major course completed research, and degree (s) obtained);</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">&nbsp; Professional record (current place of work, occupation, professional title);</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">&nbsp; Titles and dates of articles published, name of publisher and a brief description of contents;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">&nbsp; Current state of health and list of previous illnesses;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">&nbsp; Date of arrival (if known) and intended length of stay in China;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">&nbsp; Type of work and department sought in China;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">&nbsp; Details of spouse and children: name, date of birth, nationality, state of health, educational level, and whether the applicant will need to be accompanied to China;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">&nbsp; Details of any previous stays abroad, including country, type of work, and length of stay;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">&nbsp; Details of special interests, abilities, other languages known, and at what level.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">Other documents should include the following:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">&nbsp; Copies of academic and graduation certificates;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">&nbsp; Copy of certificate of employment from current place of work;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">&nbsp; A letter of recommendation from place of work or academic department;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">&nbsp; Copies of articles published;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">&nbsp; Recent certificate of health form from a certified doctor or hospital.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">At the acceptance of the appointment, for&nbsp; mail invitation letter and other documents related will be sent to your postal address. </span></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">Contact: </span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">Mr. Bai Zhenguo </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">Email:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><a href="mailto:heufao@vip.0451.com"><span style="font-family: Arial">heufao@vip.0451.com</span></a></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">Tel:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 0086 451 82568267 </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">Fax:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 0086 451 82530010 </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">Address: Foreign Affairs Office, Rm 427, Administrative Building, Harbin&nbsp; Engineering University, 145 Nantong Str., Nangang Dist., Harbin 150001, Heilongjiang Province, P.R.CHINA</span></p>', NULL, 179, 1, ''),
(150, 1, 'hrbeu', 3, 'Documents', '2009-04-29 23:30:44', '2009-04-29 23:30:44', 'hrbeu', 'Documents', 'According to the regulation, foreign experts, who plan to work in China for more than 6 months, ', '<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">Visa Application</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">Apply for Visa Z for the foreign experts who enter China for work:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">According to the regulation, foreign experts, who plan to work in China for more than 6 months, should present their work in China for more than 6 months, should present their invitation letters, valid passports and certificates, and Confirmation of Invitation of Foreign Experts (original file) to Chinese diplomatic representative organization, consulate or other overseas organizations entrusted by the Ministry of Foreign Affairs for application of Visa Z.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">Certifications necessary when applying for visa:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">To present the valid passport or other certificate(s) that can be used in place of a passport; to fill in a visa application form, and hand in recent frontal hatless half-length photos; to present documents of certification pertaining to the purposes for entry or the invitation letter from the host institution or entry or the certificate-issuing authority; those who come to China for residence of one year or more shall produce health certificates including AIDS serum examination report issued by health departments designated by the governments of the countries the applicants reside in , the health certificates shall remain valid within a period of six months as of the date of issue.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">Application for Residence Permit</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">For an expert with an employment term of one year or longer, a visa of over one-year period should be applied, and the expert is required to take an overall health checkup including AIDS test before coming to China. After entrance into China, Validation Certificate of Health examination Record of Foreigners may be obtained by presenting the Health examination Record of Foreigners to local hygienic and quarantine department. On the basis of this validation certificate and the Foreign Experts Certificate, the Public Security Organs of local regions can issue the Residence Permit to foreigners. A foreigner without health checkup and staying shorter than one year in China is allowed to receive only temporary residence permit. The foreign affairs office will apply for residence permit on behalf of the HEU foreign experts if the documents mentioned above are ready.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial">Contact:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">Mr. Bai Zhenguo </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">Email:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><a href="mailto:heufao@vip.0451.com"><span style="font-family: Arial">heufao@vip.0451.com</span></a></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">Tel:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 0086 451 82568267 </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">Fax:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 0086 451 82530010 </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">Address: Foreign Affairs Office, Rm 427, Administrative Building, Harbin&nbsp; Engineering University, 145 Nantong Str., Nangang Dist., Harbin 150001, Heilongjiang Province, P.R.CHINA</span></p>', NULL, 130, 1, ''),
(151, 1, 'hrbeu', 3, 'Regulation', '2009-04-29 23:31:47', '2009-04-29 23:31:47', 'hrbeu', 'Regulation', 'We sincerely welcome foreign experts and teachers to come to our university to work. ', '<p><span style="font-family: Arial">We sincerely welcome foreign experts and teachers to come to our university to work. And we hope that their contribution to the university will be beyond that of just teaching but also friendship building and adding cultural diversity.<br />\r\nIn order to ensure the foreign experts are satisfied (e.g. have a safe, comfortable, convenient work and living environment), this notice has been made we hope that every foreign expert follows these guidelines accordingly. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">1.The housing offered to foreign experts are only for them only, and their spouse and children to live and work. Users should&nbsp; all facilities and keep the indoor neat. Long-term residence of visitors is not allowed.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">2.If the expert''s relative comes to visit, then makes separate arrangements in the house in principle, and the expenses will be paid individually. If there are empty beds in expert''s house, the relative can live with expert but must follow the agreement of Foreign Affairs Office, and pay rent accordingly.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">3.The university offers cooking facilities in all the accommodation, but experts must pay for cooking utensils and gas expenses by themselves.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">4.All apartments are supplied with a telephone, the university is only responsible for paying teacher''s basic monthly rent of the telephone, the foreign teachers will pay their local telephone and long-distance telephone rates used by themselves.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">5.The university offers to experts the necessary transport services for airport transfer and return airport pickup. The car is also available for other purposes and can be arranged according to actual circumstances, but the experts must pay the expense by themselves.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">6.Without the permission of the university, the foreign teachers are forbidden to undertake teaching task and other work outside of the university.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">7.In order to maintain the order of the expert''s apartment and guarantee expert''s security, visiting guests (including the students) should observe relevant systems and regulations, and leaving before 10pm.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">8.During the semester, without permission, the experts are forbidden to arrange the activity on their own before vocation. The experts who leave the school more than 24 hours for some reason should notify Foreign Affairs Division one day ahead of time at least, stating destination, route, time, with pedestrian, host organization or personnel.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">9.If accommodation and other services are not satisfactory for whatever reasons please contact Foreign Affairs Office and the problem will be seen to as soon as possible.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial">Culture and education experts employed by our university should observe laws and regulations of China and other relevant systems. They should observe and abide by rules and regulations which the university makes during their time at our university. The university strives to create convenient and satisfying living arrangements for foreigners in both social and work life. The university, as able by the State Bureau of foreign experts affairs'' clause of ''foreign culture education experts condition of living benefits''.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><br />\r\n<strong>Foreign Affairs Office </strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><strong>of Harbin Engineering University</strong><br />\r\n</span></p>', NULL, 113, 1, '');
