an lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">Tel: 0086 451 82569655</font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">Email: </font></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3"><a href="mailto:changqi_yan@163.com"><span style="font-family: Arial">changqi_yan@163.com</span></a></font><span style="font-family: Arial"><font size="3"> </font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">Research Fields: nuclear power plant</font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">YAN</font><font size="3"> Changqi, Professor, born in 1955, achieved MEng from Harbin Shipbuilding Engineering Institute in 1980, and studied as a visiting scholar in McMaster University Canada from 1989 to1991, in ETH Zurich, Switzerland from 1997 to1998. His research areas include nuclear reactor thermo-hydraulics, two-phase flow and heat transfer, heat transfer enhancement. He has published books of Nuclear Reactor Engineering, Two-phase Flow, Professional English for Nuclear Engineering. The classes he teaches are Nuclear Reactor Engineering, Two-phase Flow, and Safety Heat Transfer for Nuclear Power Station. He is supervising PhD candidates in performance of nuclear power plant.</font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">Prof. Xia Hong</font></span></b></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">Tel: 0086 451 82518880</font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">Email: </font></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><a href="mailto:xiahong2005@Yahoo.com.cn" style="font-weight: normal; color: blue; text-decoration: underline; text-underline: single"><span style="font-family: Arial"><font size="3">xiahong2005@Yahoo.com.cn</font></span></a></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">Research Fields:</font></span><span lang="EN-GB" style="color: black; line-height: 150%"><font size="3"> the control and measurement of nuclear power unit</font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-GB" style="color: black"><font size="3">PhD, professor, advisor for PhD students. </font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-GB" style="color: black"><font size="3">Professor Xia has been conducting research on nuclear technology and nuclear safety since 1985. </font></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">The </font></span><span lang="EN-GB" style="color: black"><font size="3">undergraduate and postgraduate </font></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">classes he teaches are</font></span><span lang="EN-GB" style="color: black"><font size="3"> Error Theory, Intelligent Instrument, Thermal Testing Technology, Nuclear Engineering Inspection Technology, Fault Detection and Diagnosis, Intelligent Detection and Data Fusion. She has published one text book and one&nbsp; research monograph. </font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-GB" style="color: black"><font size="3">Professor Xia has been a principle investigator in several defence feasibility studies. Among them, one was awarded the first class prize and the other five were awarded the third class prizes by ministries. She made some contributions to apply correlation theory to measurement technology. For the Fault Detection of the Nuclear Power Unit, a fault detection and diagnosis method is proposed based on data fusion theory. A data fusion functional model and a calculation model, which highly summarized the essence and key technologies of this approach, are established from the perspective of system theory. </font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-GB" style="color: black"><font size="3">She has published more than 30 papers in international conferences and engineering journals as Nuclear Science and Technology, Nuclear Power Engineering and Journal of Harbin Engineering Journal. She has supervised 18 master students with 12 of them received their master degrees. There are four doctoral students currently under her supervision.</font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-GB" style="color: black"><font size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">Prof. Han Weishi</font></span></b></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">Tel: 0086 451 82838188</font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">Email: </font></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><a href="mailto:wshan@public.hr.hl.cn" style="font-weight: normal; color: blue; text-decoration: underline; text-underline: single"><span style="font-family: Arial"><font size="3">wshan@public.hr.hl.cn</font></span></a></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">Research Fields: nuclear dynamics for ships</font></span><span style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">；</font></span><span lang="en-us"><font size="3">n</font></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">uclear dynamic device</font></span><span style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">；</font></span><span lang="en-us"><font size="3">n</font></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">uclear radiation detection</font></span><span style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">；<span lang="en-us">p</span></font></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">rotection and environmental protection.</font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoPlainText" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US"><font size="3">Han Weishi, born in 1949, graduated with a master&rsquo;s degree from the department of Nuclear Dynamic Equipment in Harbin Ship Engineering College in 1982. He is now a professor, the doctor&rsquo;s tutor, member of the Chinese Nuclear Society, the executive member of the Chinese Nuclear Industry Education Society and the head of Energy Resource Engineering and Technology Institute affiliated to the Institute of Engineering and Technology Design.</font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoPlainText" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US"><font size="3">He performs his teaching and research activities mainly in the field of nuclear engineering. The classes he has been teaching include Thermo-hydraulics of Nuclear Reactor,&nbsp; Nuclear Reactor Engineering, Nuclear Dynamic Equipment, Seal Material and Structure Design and Nuclear Reactor Engineering Design. He has been dedicated to the research of the nuclear dynamics for ships. He has won the third class prize for eight times, one for the National Invention and six for Innovations in Science and Technology granted by China State Shipbuilding Corporation and Commission of Science Technology and Industry for National Defense.</font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoPlainText" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US"><font size="3">Now he leads a research team in the projects of Miniature Nuclear Dynamic Integrated Experimental Device, Nuclear Radiation Detection and Protection supported by the ''211 Project''. At present his research is centered upon nuclear dynamic device, nuclear radiation detection and protection and environmental protection. In recent years, he has about 20 papers published in journals such as Nuclear Power Engineering and Ship Engineering.</font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoPlainText" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="en-us"><font size="3">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">Prof. Sun Zhongning</font></span></b></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">Tel: 0086 451 82569655</font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">Email: </font></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3"><a href="mailto:zhongningsun@yahoo.com.cn"><span style="font-family: Arial">zhongningsun@yahoo.com.cn</span></a></font><span style="font-family: Arial"><font size="3"> </font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US"><font size="3">Research Fields:</font><span style="color: black"><font size="3"> passive safety system for advanced reactor, mechanism of convective heat transfer with and without phase change, flow boiling and convective heat transfer in narrow channel, enhancement of heat transfer, and gas-liquid two phase flow. </font></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="color: black"><font size="3">Sun Zhongning, born in Shandong Province, in March 1963. He received his MEng degree in Nuclear Engineering in 1990 from Harbin Shipbuilding Engineering Institute and PhD in Marine Engineering in 2000 from Harbin Engineering University. Now he acts as professor and doctoral advisor at the College of Nuclear Science and Technology in HEU. He teaches at both undergraduate and graduate levels in the classes of Nuclear Power Equipment, Advanced Nuclear Reactor and Thermofluid Dynamics. Published more than 50 papers and 1 monograph. </font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial">&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">Prof. Shi Xiaocheng</font></span></b></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">Tel: 0086 451 82519306-2312</font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">Email: </font></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3"><a href="mailto:shixiaocheng@hrbeu.edu.cn"><span style="font-family: Arial">shixiaocheng@hrbeu.edu.cn</span></a></font><span style="font-family: Arial"><font size="3"> </font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3">Research Fields:</font></span><span lang="EN-US" style="layout-grid-mode: line; line-height: 150%"><font size="3"> vessel control, underwater control and nuclear power plant control areas</font></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="3"> </font></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify"><span lang="EN-US"><font size="3">Shi Xiaocheng, is</font></span><span lang="EN-GB"><font size="3"> a professor and doctoral advisor at </font></span><span lang="EN-US"><font size="3">Harbin Engineering University</font></span><span lang="EN-GB"><font size="3">. </font></span><span class="bodytext1"><span lang="EN-US"><font size="3">H</font></span><span lang="EN-GB"><font size="3">e was </font></span></span><span lang="EN-US"><font size="3">born in August of 1957 and <span class="bodytext1">started his career in 1974. </span>He has been entitled as Youth Specialist with Prominent Contribution<span class="bodytext1"> by the </span>Commission of Science</font></span> <span lang="EN-US">Technology and Industry for National Defense and Excellent Youth Scientist by China State Shipbuilding Corporation. He is enjoying government special allowance and has won more than 10 times of Science &amp; Technology Progress Award above ministerial level, which includes 1 third class prize of the national award, 3 first class, 4 second class and 2 third class prizes of ministerial level; he also received the 2004 Youth Award of Science and Technology of Harbin City. He has composed over 20 Science and Technology Reports for National Defense, and published over 50 papers in journals and international conferences, 12 of which has been indexed by EI, ISTP and SA.</span></p>\r\n<p class="Normal" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0px; vertical-align: bottom; line-height: normal; text-align: justify"><span lang="EN-US" style="layout-grid-mode: line; font-family: Times New Roman"><font size="3">Prof. Shi Xiaocheng has won Excellent Awards in Postgraduate Teaching for many times during his over 20 years&rsquo; work in teaching, scientific research and discipline construction. As the technique director of the systems or equipments, he has undertaken up to 16 developments of the national mandatory scientific research programs and made lots of achievements in R&amp;D in vessel control, underwater control and nuclear power plant control.</font></span><span id="1240989589429E" style="display: none">&nbsp;</span></p>', NULL, 217, 1, ''),
