</span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td align="center" width="86" height="22">\r\n            <p><span lang="EN-GB" style="color: black; font-family: Times New Roman"><font size="1">08:00 to 11:30 14:00 to 22:00</font></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td height="22">\r\n            <p><span lang="EN-GB" style="color: black; font-family: Times New Roman"><font size="1">08:00 to 11:30&nbsp;&nbsp; 14:00 to 17:00</font></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td width="267">\r\n            <p align="justify"><span lang="EN-US" style="color: black; font-family: Times New Roman"><font size="1">Audio &amp; Video Materials Room</font></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td width="87">\r\n            <p align="justify"><span lang="EN-US" style="color: black; font-family: Times New Roman"><font size="1">Rm414 &amp; 415 </font></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td align="center" width="86">\r\n            <p><span lang="EN-GB" style="color: black; font-family: Times New Roman"><font size="1">08:00 to 11:30 14:00 to 22:00</font></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td>\r\n            <p><span lang="EN-GB" style="color: black; font-family: Times New Roman"><font size="1">08:00 to 11:30&nbsp;&nbsp; 14:00 to 17:00</font></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td width="267">\r\n            <p align="justify"><span lang="EN-GB" style="color: black; font-family: Times New Roman"><font size="1">CD (Accompany to Books) Loan Desk</font></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td width="87">\r\n            <p align="justify"><span lang="EN-GB" style="color: black; font-family: Times New Roman"><font size="1">Rm416</font></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td align="center" width="86">\r\n            <p><span lang="EN-GB" style="color: black; font-family: Times New Roman"><font size="1">08:00 to 11.30 14:00 to 17:30</font></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td>\r\n            <p><span lang="EN-GB" style="color: black; font-family: Times New Roman"><font size="1">08:00 to 11:30&nbsp;&nbsp; 14:00 to 17:00</font></span></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</p>\r\n<p align="justify"><font face="Times New Roman" size="1"><b>Note: </b></font><font face="Times New Roman" style="font-size: 11pt">*</font><font size="1"><span lang="EN-US" style="color: black; font-family: Times New Roman">closed on 8:00</span><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"> to </span></font><span lang="EN-US" style="color: black; font-family: Times New Roman"><font size="1">12:00 Wed. for machine maintenance</font></span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span lang="en-us"><font size="1"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; **</span></font></span><span lang="EN-GB" style="color: black; font-family: Times New Roman"><font size="1">closed on Saturday<br />\r\n</font></span><font face="Times New Roman" style="font-size: 11pt"><br />\r\n<img height="150" alt="" hspace="20" width="234" border="1" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/Administration_and_Service_Departments/pic/l1.jpg" /></font></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><strong><font style="font-size: 11pt">Rules of compensation for book loss or defilement</font>&nbsp;</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">Readers must take good care of books and periodicals you have borrowed in the library. You will compensate for them if you lose or damage them.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><strong><span lang="EN-US">Loss compensation </span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">In case you have lost a book or a periodical you borrowed, you will will be required to try and purchase the same book or periodical (the same edition, the same volume date) that you have lost and after that you can go through the compensation formality in the library. If you can not purchase the same book or periodical of the same edition, you should compensate for it according to the following standard:</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">Compensate for 4 times of original cost for general books.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">Compensate for 6 times of original cost for instrumental books and periodicals, foreign language ones and valuable ones with only two copies. </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">Compensate for 10 times of original cost for Chinese and foreign language books and periodicals with only one copy in library. </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">Compensate for 10 times of original cost for one copy (book, collection) of many periodicals.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">Compensate for each page for those books and periodicals without the price or published before 1989: 0.08 yuan RMB each page for B5 of Chinese ones; 0.04 yuan RMB each page for A4; 0.1 yuan RMB each page for B5 of photocopied foreign language ones; 5 yuan RMB each page for foreign language books and periodicals, colored albums and picture collections of original edition in any format; also add 5 yuan RMB as binding fee for various kinds of deluxe books and periodicals. if you find your lost book within two moths after the compensation, you can ask the refund at the Library Card Center.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">You will not receive&nbsp; refund if you lost the compensation receipt or later than 2 months or more have passed since payment. Then you have to pay 1yuan as service charge when you go through the refund formality and at the same time you must pay overdue fine calculated from compensation date to refund date according to relevant overdue rules.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><strong><span lang="EN-US">Defilement compensation </span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;When borrowing books or periodicals, readers must carefully check out whether the copy is complete and clean. If you find the copy has been torn, but with no signs as&nbsp; ''torn'' or ''skipping leaf'' in it, please contact a librarian before you borrow. Otherwise, if you borrow a originally torn copy with no statement signs, you should compensate for it.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">As in the case of lose of books, if any part of the book is torn (including charts or adjoining pages), or text with serious defilements that hinders other readers'' reading, or over 5 pages with mark, note, written answers are considered as the behavior of defiling the whole book. In this case, the user will compensate for his behavior according to article 1 in loss-compensation rules. </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">The user will compensate the original cost of the book for defilements and small amount of marks or writings that are not serious and do not hinder other users'' reading. </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">The user who causes front cover or back cover to come off but does not defile the text will compensate for 40% of original cost of the book.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">Code of Conduct</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US"><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n</span></span></span><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">Smoking, eating, drinking and noise, including conversation within the silent areas, and other&nbsp; improper conduct are prohibited. Food and drink must not be brought into the Library. </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">Mobiles, pagers and personal audio equipment must be switched off before entering the Library. </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">Writing in or otherwise defacing, or damaging, Library property is prohibited. </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">All users must leave the Library promptly when the library is closing or any other reason for evacuating the building is signaled. </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US"><img height="140" alt="" width="301" border="1" src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/Administration_and_Service_Departments/pic/l2.jpg" /></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">Regulation on Library Card</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">The library card is valid membership identification to borrow and read books. The library members are supposed to show their card when borrowing or reading books/periodicals in the library. </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">The following persons are eligible for membership of the Library: members of the staff of the University and registered students of the University (general sort).</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">The membership and library card application and other related services are offered in the Library Card Center on 2nd floor of the library. The opening hours are 8:00-11:30 and 14:00-17:30 from Monday to Friday. At provision of the applicant''s student ID (or Staff ID), one standard photo (1 inch) and 10yuan (card cost) the applicant may apply for a library card. </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">The registered students besides the groups defined in 2 shall pay 300 yuan RMB as a deposit. </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">A new IC library card is set with a universal access password. It is suggested to reset the password with eight Arabic numerals in the Library Card Center after cards being issued. Members of the Library will be held-responsible failure to reset their new password in time. </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">Please try and remember your library card password as it is required when taking a loan and wrong inputs will lead to the card-reading machine eating your card. In case the card password is forgotten, the card holder may apply for password recall service in the Card office,&nbsp; and service fee of 1 yuan RMB will required.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">You must take good care of your library card. Once you lose it, you can apply for a new one in the Library Card Center on 2nd floor of the library with unit (or department) confirmation letter, your own student ID (or Labor ID), one photo of one inch without hat or hair cover and 10 yuan RMB for card cost .</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">The library card can only be used&nbsp; by yourself. You can not lend it to others otherwise the library will detain your card for half year, and you and the user who uses your card in your name have to individually pay for the fines 10 yuan RMB. For those who borrow books using the other''s card without permission, they will be regarded and fined as book-stealers.&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">Keep IC borrowing card clear, keep it far from high temperature, magnetic field and water source. Avoid machine abrasion or breakage.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">Check out the books when you borrow them and state the breakage, slipped page or mark to the librarian, otherwise you must compensate for these yourself. </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">Remember the borrowing date otherwise you will be be given an overdue fee.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial"><span style="font-size: larger"><span lang="EN-US">Return your borrowing card to the library before your departure from the university.</span></span></span></p>', NULL, 905, 1, ''),
(222, 1, 'hrbeu', 11, 'HEU Periodicals Publishing Department', '2009-04-30 00:56:06', '2009-06-30 10:30:37', 'hrbeu', 'HEU Periodicals Publishing Department', 'HEU Periodicals Publishing Department', '<p style="text-align: right"><strong><a href="http://xuebao.hrbeu.edu.cn/">Department Homepage</a></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Introduction</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\nHEU Periodicals Publishing Department is one of the editing and publishing departments of Harbin Engineering University. It is mainly responsible for the edition and publication of 4 kinds of journals: Journal of Harbin Engineering University, Journal of Marine Science and Application, Applied Science and Technology and CAAI Transactions on Intelligent Systems. The present director is Xu Ruobing.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Journal of Harbin Engineering University&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Journal of Harbin Engineering University, established in 1980, is published bimonthly in Chinese by HEU. It covers science and engineering, and takes shipping industry, ocean&nbsp; exploitation and national defense as a notable feature, including naval architecture, marine power engineering, nuclear energy engineering, underwater acoustical engineering, and automatic control, etc.</p>\r\n<p>ISSN 1006-7043&nbsp; CN 23-1390/U&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Subscription code: 14-111</p>\r\n<p>Tel: 0086 451 82519357/ 82534001</p>\r\n<p>E-mail: <a href="mailto:heuxb@vip.sina.com">heuxb@vip.sina.com</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.heuxb.com">http://www.heuxb.com</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>Journal of Marine Science and Application</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\nJournal of Marine Science and Application is an English publication of HEU. It started in 2002. It is supervised by the Chinese Commission of Science Technology and Industry for National Defense and is edited by HEU. This journal is a comprehensive academic journal that focuses on ship industry, naval equipment and technology, ocean exploitation and nuclear energy application. It aims at enhancing international academic exchanges and driving national shipping technology for further development. It contains ship engineering, nuclear energy engineering, underwater acoustic engineering, automatic control, mechanical and electrical engineering and computer application.</p>\r\n<p>ISSN1671-9433&nbsp; CN1505/T</p>\r\n<p>Subscription code: 14-323</p>\r\n<p>Price (domestic): RMB &yen; 20.00</p>\r\n<p>E-mail: <a href="mailto:enxb@jmsa.com.cn">enxb@jmsa.com.cn</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.jmsa.com.cn">http://www.jmsa.com.cn</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>Applied Science and Technology</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\nApplied Science and Technology is a technical journal promoting new technology, new product and new craft, which aims at transmitting technical information rapidly and promoting the transform of achievement. It is supervised by the Chinese Commission of Science Technology and Industry for National Defense and is edited by Harbin Engineering University. It is a monthly journal.</p>\r\n<p>ISSN 1009-671X&nbsp; CN 23-1191/U</p>\r\n<p>Subscription code: 14-323</p>\r\n<p>E-mail: <a href="mailto:heuyykj@vip.sina.com">heuyykj@vip.sina.com</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.yykj.cn">http://www.yykj.cn</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>CAAI Transactions on Intelligent Systems</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\nCAAI Transactions on Intelligent Systems is one of transactions of Chinese Association for Artificial Intelligence. It is established in 2006 and published bimonthly by HEU.</p>\r\n<p>The journal is supervised by Commission of Science Technology and Industry for National Defense and sponsored by Harbin Engineering University in combination with Chinese Association for Artificial Intelligence. It mainly publishes the newest researches and high level academic papers in the field of intelligence science, including artificial intelligence and computation intelligence, intelligence control and decisions, intelligence information processing, expert systems and knowledge projects, machine learning, knowledge discovering, artificial psychology, machine feelings, etc.</p>\r\n<p>ISSN 1673-4785&nbsp; CN23-1538/TP</p>\r\n<p>Subscription code: 14-161</p>\r\n<p>E-mail: <a href="mailto:tis@vip.sina.com">tis@vip.sina.com</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.tis.net.cn">http://www.tis.net.cn</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>Contacts Us</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nTel: 0086&nbsp; 451 82519357</p>\r\n<p>Fax: 0086 451 82534001</p>\r\n<p>Location: Administration Building ,Harbin Engineering University, 145 Nantong Street, Harbin 150001, P.R.CHINA</p>', NULL, 892, 1, ''),
(223, 1, 'hrbeu', 11, 'Physical Education Department', '2009-04-30 00:56:48', '2009-06-30 10:32:15', 'hrbeu', 'Physical Education Department', 'Physical Education Department', '<p style="text-justify: inter-ideograph; layout-grid-mode: char; text-align: right"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b><a href="http://gongxue.cn/tixunbu/index.asp">Department Homepage</a></b></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-justify: inter-ideograph; layout-grid-mode: char; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b>Department Introduction</b></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-justify: inter-ideograph; layout-grid-mode: char; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US">The Physical Education Department was set up in 1987, mainly undertaking the entire school physical education tasks, organizing sports competition and scientific research in the related areas. The Department organized to Establish the university student sports association in 1995, which has developed 17 single items sports teams. The Department also holds track and field games, the sports culture festival every year to enhance campus culture, whose attendance reaches 70,000 people every year. Under the faculty''s hard work, the University''s pass rate in the national University student physique healthy tests maintains 98% or higher. The Department was awarded with the National Sports Work Advanced Unit by th</span><span lang="EN-US">e National Sports Bureau</span><span lang="EN-US">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-justify: inter-ideograph; layout-grid-mode: char; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b>Staff</b></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-justify: inter-ideograph; layout-grid-mode: char; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US">The Department has </span><span lang="EN-US">71</span><span lang="EN-US"> academic and administrative staff,&nbsp; including </span><span lang="EN-US">5</span><span lang="EN-US"> professor&nbsp; people, </span><span lang="EN-US">and 19 </span><span lang="EN-US">associate professor (</span><span lang="EN-US">20 teachers having </span><span lang="EN-US">master and doctorate degrees).&nbsp; In 2003 the Department established the master program of sports education and training study in the specializing directions of&nbsp; speed skating, the basketball, the swimming, the school sports study, the physiology of exercise.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-justify: inter-ideograph; layout-grid-mode: char; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b>Research</b></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-justify: inter-ideograph; layout-grid-mode: char; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US">In 2005 HEU''s physical education curriculum was evaluated as the provincial high-quality curriculum. The scientific research work obtains the unprecedented progress, in the recent five years, the faculty has publish </span><span lang="EN-US">326 </span><span lang="EN-US">papers in all levels of academic publications, </span><span lang="EN-US">35</span><span lang="EN-US"> teaching material, and </span><span lang="EN-US">7</span><span lang="EN-US">audio and video teaching materials. The Department was awarded with </span><span lang="EN-US">two provincial </span><span lang="EN-US">first awards, and </span><span lang="EN-US">three</span><span lang="EN-US"> second-level awards.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-justify: inter-ideograph; layout-grid-mode: char; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b>Contact us</b></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-justify: inter-ideograph; layout-grid-mode: char; text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b>\r\n<table id="table1" width="100%" border="1">\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td align="left" width="140"><span lang="FR" style="font-weight: 700; font-family: Times New Roman"><font size="2">Dean</font></span></td>\r\n            <td align="left"><font size="2"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman">0086 451 </span><span lang="FR" style="font-family: Times New Roman">82518588</span></font></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td align="left" width="140"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-weight: 700; font-family: ''Times New Roman''"><font size="2">Deputy Dean</font></span></td>\r\n            <td align="left"><font size="2"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman">0086 451 </span></font><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: ''Times New Roman''"><font size="2">82519448</font></span></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td align="left" width="140"><b><font face="Times New Roman" size="2">Administration Office</font></b></td>\r\n            <td align="left"><font size="2"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman">0086 451 </span></font><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: ''Times New Roman''"><font size="2">82519856</font></span></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td align="left" width="140"><b><font face="Times New Roman" size="2">Location</font></b></td>\r\n            <td align="left"><font face="Times New Roman" size="2">HEU Recreation Center</font></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</b></span></p>', NULL, 857, 1, ''),
(224, 1, 'hrbeu', 29, 'Center Introduction', '2009-04-30 05:07:18', '2009-04-30 05:07:18', 'hrbeu', 'Center Introduction', 'Center Introduction', '<div class="Section1">\r\n<p align="justify"><b><span lang="EN-GB">Introduction: </span></b></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span lang="EN-US">In order to meet the needs of reform in the education of the University, we train students'' initiative spirit and comprehensive practice ability and improve students'' overall qualities. The University established the Engineering Training Center in May,2003, which is the students'' practice and teaching base and offers a complete, systematic platform for students'' practice and teaching.</span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><img src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/Academic_Departments/Project_Training_Centre/pic/2.gif" width="235" height="191" alt="" /><img src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/Academic_Departments/Project_Training_Centre/pic/3.jpg" width="239" height="191" alt="" /><img src="http://english.hrbeu.edu.cn/Academic_Departments/Project_Training_Centre/pic/2.jpg" width="259" height="191" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><b><span lang="EN-US">Our Experience:</span></b></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span lang="EN-US">In 2003, the Center finished primary training for freshmen in 95 classes and project comprehensive training for sophomores in 89 classes, totally 16,000 students. According to the educational and teaching guidelines of the University, the Center has designed and developed a series of project training syllabuses, and teaching arrangements, which have been well-accepted by the students and being referred by other universities. The staff are working to manage the Center in a more scientific and efficient way, and make all their efforts to serve the students. Various theme activities for staff and students are organized routinely, like workshop, presentation competition, etc., and both the faculty and the students are gaining improvement through the flexible methods.</span></p>\r\n</div>', NULL, 97, 1, ''),
