(244, 1, 'hrbeu', 30, 'Professional Master of Engineering in Naval Architecture and Ocean Engineering', '2009-05-02 04:42:49', '2009-05-02 04:42:49', 'hrbeu', 'Professional Master of Engineering in Naval Architecture and Ocean Engineering', 'Professional Master of Engineering in Naval Architecture and Ocean Engineering', '<p align="justify"><b>Introduction: </b><span lang="EN-US">The Department of Naval Architecture and Ocean Engineering (NAOE) at the Shipbuilding Engineering College has a history of more than 50 years. Primitively, established as Navy Engineering Department, it was one of the key departments of Harbin Military Engineering Institute, set up in 1953. The College serves in educating high caliber researchers, technicians and engineers through meticulous studies and rigorous practices of relevant subjects. In regard to educational training, scientific and </span><span lang="EN-US">technical research and engineering design, this department is ranked as one of the leading institutions of the country and thus enjoys the fame as ''China''s shipbuilding engineers'' cradle''.</span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><b>Facilities: </b>The College has four related laboratories, including Multi-functional Ship Model Towing Tank, Horizontal Water Circulation Trough, Engineering Structure Test Lab, and a Ship CAD/CAM Lab. They are furnished with advanced photometric and electrometric devices, data acquisition and analysis systems, multi-condition loading structure test bed etc. The total assets amount to over 80 million RMB (or $ 10 M).</p>\r\n<p align="justify"><b>Research: </b>In scientific researches, the faculty mainly engages in investigations, design and developing of advanced and high-performance vehicles and marine engineering structures. As the results of their efforts, some achievements in the areas of hydrodynamics and structural mechanics of ships, such as resistance, propulsion, maneuverability, sea-keeping, wave loading, strength and fatigue of naval and offshore engineering structures, have made great progress, and many works have reached to the leading level in China. Some researches of those subjects have approached the corresponding world advanced levels; among them are the studies on hydrodynamics of advanced high performance vessels, ship stabilization technique, high efficiency propulsion, and ocean energy utilization, energy saving technology, under-water robotics technology, submersible design technology, ship wave loading, structural hydro-elasticity theory and experiment.</p>\r\n<p align="justify"><b>Achievements: </b>This CSE is the member organization of ITTC (International Towing Tank Conference), and ISSC (International Ship Structural Mechanics Conference), the top academic organizations in shipbuilding. Young and middle-aged faculty members are encouraged and supported to take part actively in international academic activities. Teachers go abroad for attending academic meetings and conferences each year, they exchange experience with foreign colleagues and promote friendship worldwide, building up a good reputation of CSE in home and abroad.</p>\r\n<p align="justify"><b>Research Fields:</b></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<ol>\r\n    <li>\r\n    <p align="justify">Ship Design</p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n    <p align="justify">Ship Structure Performance</p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n    <p align="justify">Ship Fluid Performance</p>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p align="justify"><b>Core classes: </b>Numerical Methods, Math. Phy. Equ, Ship Design I, Ship Marine Hydrodynamics, Under Water Vessels, Elastic-Plastic Mechanics, Chinese Language, Advanced Fluid Mechanics, Ship Resistance, Ship Propulsion, Ship Sea-keeping, Ship Maneuverability, Ship Design II, Finite Element Method in Structure Analysis, Stress in Shells, Structure Strength Assessment</p>', NULL, 69, 1, ''),
(245, 1, 'hrbeu', 31, 'Bachelor in Aerocraft Propusion Engineering', '2009-05-02 04:43:18', '2009-05-02 04:43:18', 'hrbeu', 'Bachelor in Aerocraft Propusion Engineering', 'Bachelor in Aerocraft Propusion Engineering', '<p>Bachelor in Aerocraft Propusion Engineering</p>', NULL, 2, 0, ''),
(246, 1, 'hrbeu', 31, 'Bachelor in Building Environment and Equipment Engineering', '2009-05-02 04:44:03', '2009-05-02 04:44:03', 'hrbeu', 'Bachelor in Building Environment and Equipment Engineering', 'Bachelor in Building Environment and Equipment Engineering', '<div class="Section1" style="layout-grid:  15.6pt none">\r\n<p align="justify"><b><span lang="EN-US">Introduction: </span></b><span lang="EN-US">We are committed to train and educate senior engineering technicians, who have basic theoretical knowledge and ability in designing, installing, operating and managing of indoors environmental equipment system and architectural public facility system in or related to designing research institute, architectural engineering companies and property management companies. This Program is also open for international students.</span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span lang="EN-US">This Program focuses on heating, ventilating and air-conditioner engineering technology. The students are encouraged to master basic theories and knowledge about construction physics environment and environment controlling system. The Program arranges basic training on designing, installing and debugging, and operating and managing of construction environmental equipment system.</span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><b><span lang="EN-US">Research: </span></b><span lang="EN-US">Today, people tend to attach much more importance to control and management of industry and living environment; meanwhile. With the rapid development of construction industry, there are a great demands for technicians in this area. The Program was established to satisfy such demands. The Program has sufficient faculty resource and lab resources. </span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><b><span lang="EN-US">Graduates'' career prospects: </span></b><span lang="EN-US">The graduates can find jobs in designing and research units in the fields of construction designing and municipal engineering. They can work on the designing, researching, installing, property managing of public facility systems and construction heating supply systems.</span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><b><span lang="EN-US">Core classes: </span></b><span lang="EN-US">heat transferring, engineering thermodynamics, engineering fluid mechanics, self-control principle, mechanics principle, electric &amp; electronic technique, architectural environment, thermal conversion principle &amp; its equipment, fluid piping arrangement, air-conditioner piping, heating engineering, refrigeration technique, construction principle &amp; organization and so on.</span></p>\r\n</div>', NULL, 160, 1, ''),
(247, 1, 'hrbeu', 31, 'Bachelor in Civil Engineering', '2009-05-02 04:44:36', '2009-05-02 04:44:36', 'hrbeu', 'Bachelor in Civil Engineering', 'Bachelor in Civil Engineering', '<p align="justify"><span lang="en-us" style="font-weight: 700">Introduction</span><font style="font-weight: 700"><span lang="EN-US">: </span></font><span lang="EN-US">We are committed to train and educate senior engineering technicians to master the basic theory and knowledge of engineering mechanics, fluid mechanics, rock mechanics and structural design, who have the ability to work on the planning, designing, scientific developing, constructing and managing of civil engineering projects in house-building engineering, highways and city roads engineering, bridge engineering, tunnel and underground engineering and airfield engineering. </span>This Program is also open for international students.</p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-weight: 700">Research: </span><span lang="EN-US">Because of its great strength, this discipline has been authorized to award both the master''s and doctor''s degrees in solid mechanics and to award the master''s degree in structural engineering. Its primary researches are involved in elastic wave and its application in earthquake engineering &amp; shock structure engineering, elastic-plastic fractural mechanics and its elastic deformation and variation method, optimum structuring and theory of construction reliability and its application, reinforced concrete structure, steel structure, structural emulation system and so on.</span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><b><span lang="EN-US">The suitable career fields for the graduates: </span></b><span lang="EN-US">Most of the graduates will choose the Building Industry Head Corporation of China and construction enterprises of civil engineering, architectural designing research institute, universities and colleges, urban construction department and real estate development agency in some of the coastal cities.</span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-weight: 700">Core classes: </span><span lang="EN-US">theoretical mechanics, material mechanics, structural mechanics, rock mechanics, fluid mechanics, concrete structure, </span><span lang="EN-US">masonry structure</span>,<span lang="EN-US"> steel structure, house architecture, construction technology of civil engineering, construction budget of civil engineering, organization and management of engineering items, survey of civil engineering, architectural Auto CAD, PKPM structure CAD, shock structure designing, bridge structure and track survey &amp; designing.</span></p>', NULL, 274, 1, ''),
(248, 1, 'hrbeu', 31, 'Bachelor in Engineering Mechanics', '2009-05-02 04:44:58', '2009-05-09 01:48:09', 'hrbeu', 'Bachelor in Engineering Mechanics', 'Bachelor in Engineering Mechanics', '<div id="result_box" dir="ltr" style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: small">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Program is committed to&nbsp;cultivate students with&nbsp;theoretical knowledge of mechanics, numerical computation and experimental skills, able to work in a variety of practical (such as machinery, construction, materials, energy, transportation, aerospace, marine, water, chemicals, etc.) and mechanics, engaged in the research, technological development , engineering mechanics teaching of computing and high-level engineering and technical personnel.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Main courses: Theoretical mechanics, material mechanics, fluid mechanics, elasticity, plasticity mechanics, analytical mechanics, structural mechanics, mechanics, mathematical methods, based on vibration, structural vibration, nonlinear vibration, random vibration, structural and engineering software applications, experimental mechanics, dynamic testing methods.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Students can choose elective courses either&nbsp;of professional mechanics&nbsp;and general mechanics&nbsp;or of&nbsp;engineering mechanics according to their own professional and interest.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Through the professional courses of study, graduates&nbsp;will have&nbsp;a solid foundation, a systematic grasp of the broad fields of theoretical basis for technology, including solid mechanics, general mechanics, engineering mechanics and fluid dynamics and other basic knowledge; with strong&nbsp;problem solving ability for&nbsp;mechanical engineering-related problems from a theoretical analysis, numerical calculation and the ability of modern science experiment; with strong computer and foreign language capabilities.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></div>', NULL, 109, 1, ''),
(249, 1, 'hrbeu', 31, 'Bachelor in Flight Vehicle Design and Engineering', '2009-05-02 04:45:26', '2009-05-02 04:45:26', 'hrbeu', 'Bachelor in Flight Vehicle Design and Engineering', 'Bachelor in Flight Vehicle Design and Engineering', '<p align="justify"><b>Introduction: </b>We are committed to train and educate advanced engineering technicians to master the basic theory and knowledge about engineering mechanics, fluid mechanics and vehicle master designing, structural designing &amp; researching, structure strength analyzing &amp; experimenting of the vehicle and general mechanical designing and manufacturing. This Program is also open for international students.</p>\r\n<p align="justify"><b>Graduates'' career prospects:</b> Since the formal enrollment in 1978, many of our graduates have become chief designers, researchers, senior engineers in astronautics and missiles, making great contributions to our aircraft and aerospace industry and national defense industry, most graduates go to enterprises and institutions of the national defense industry, aircraft and aerospace designing institutes, research institutes, designing institutes, universities to work on the researching, designing and managing of vehicle designing engineering.</p>\r\n<p align="justify"><b>Core classes: </b>material mechanics, mechanical design, elastic mechanics, vibration theory, fluid mechanics, aerodynamics, vehicle dynamics, flight dynamics, automatic control theory, master design of vehicle, space guidance control, heat transfer and thermal protection.</p>', NULL, 151, 1, ''),
(250, 1, 'hrbeu', 31, 'Bachelor in Water Supply and Sewerage Engineering', '2009-05-02 04:45:54', '2009-05-02 04:45:54', 'hrbeu', 'Bachelor in Water Supply and Sewerage Engineering', 'Bachelor in Water Supply and Sewerage Engineering', '<div class="Section1" style="layout-grid:  15.6pt none">\r\n<p align="justify"><b><span lang="en-us">Introduction: </span></b><span lang="EN-US">We are committed to train and educate senior engineering technicians of water supply and drainage engineering, who master basic knowledge about municipal water supply engineering, drainage works, water supply &amp; drainage engineering, industry water supply and drainage engineering, water-contamination controlling and resource protection. This Program offers basic training in computer technique and contamination charting. </span>This Program is also open for international students.</p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span lang="en-us"><b>G</b></span><b><span lang="EN-US">raduates'' career prospects:</span></b><span lang="EN-US"><b>&nbsp;</b> With the rapid development of the economy and the higher requirement of the environment protection, both the municipal construction and industrial and mining enterprises need a large number of senior technicians in water supply and drainage engineering. Thus, the Program provides a promising prospect for personnel training and researches in water supply and drainage engineering. The graduates can work in the areas of water supply engineering, drainage engineering, constructing engineering, municipal engineering, researching engineering. </span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span lang="EN-US"><b>Core classes:</b> common chemistry, physical chemistry, engineering mechanics, measuring, engineering drawing, microbiology, hydraulics, electronics, construction water supply &amp; drainage, water supply treatment, sewage disposal, water supply &amp; drainage of high-building, water supply network, drainage engineering network, water pump and pump station.</span></p>\r\n</div>', NULL, 165, 1, ''),
