(276, 1, 'hrbeu', 32, 'Master in Marine Engine Engineering', '2009-05-02 05:59:33', '2009-05-02 05:59:33', 'hrbeu', 'Master in Marine Engine Engineering', 'Master in Marine Engine Engineering', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt"><span style="font-size: larger"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b>Introduction: </b><span lang="EN-US">In this discipline there are 19 teachers (15 Professors, 2 Associate Professors and 2 lectures, including 12 PhD holders) who have conducted research on Marine Engineering for a long time. Four special research areas have dominant position in China, focusing on the performance and system analysis for ship power plant totality, vibration and noise control for ship power plants, automatic and measurement for ship power plants and special power plants. The four areas mentioned above are also the foster directions for this master program. Marine Engine Engineering is a synthetically discipline of advanced science and technology, centralized on thermal, mechanical, electrical and automation engineering to train excellent students who deal with design, maintenance, management and research on ship power plants. This discipline was based on the faculty of warship internal combustion engine (established in 1953) of Harbin Military Institute - HMI, marine gas turbine (established in 1958 HMI) and so on. There are more than 50 research projects (including 30 of them were completed, 20 of them had awards from the government and 20 of them are conducting now) and total funds of them are 76.25 Million RMB. In the ''10th Five-year Plan'', this Program is constructed under the full support of HEU, pursuing research on the internal combustion engine, gas turbine engine and combined power plants. The master students of Marine Engine take part in these researches. There are five important laboratories: marine internal combustion engine lab, marine power plant vibration &amp; noise control lab, combined power plant lab, steam power plant lab, and special power plant lab. In this discipline, there is some application software also. These facilities are the research basements for training the masters. </span><span lang="EN-US">The classes of this Program can be lectured in English.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt"><span style="font-size: larger"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b><span lang="en-us">Major benefits for students</span></b><span lang="EN-US"><b>: </b>The students will master the main fundamental theories of this discipline, possess the ability of using the basic theories to solve practical engineering problems.<span style="color: red"> </span>According to the 4 areas mentioned above some compulsory classes, 22 electives are available for students and some other classes supplied by other colleges are also available. During the first semester of the first year students should pass the common theoretical classes and during the second semester and the third semester the students should pass the compulsory classes and some electives to meet their thesis requirements. Total 32 class credits must be obtained for each student who will be allowed to start the thesis.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt"><span style="font-size: larger"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b><span lang="EN-US">Research Fields</span>:</b></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt; text-indent: -24pt; margin-left: 24pt"><span style="font-size: larger"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US">(1) The performance and system analysis for ship power plant</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt"><span style="font-size: larger"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US">(2) Vibration and noise control for ship power plants</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt"><span style="font-size: larger"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US">(3) Automatic and measurement for ship power plants</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt"><span style="font-size: larger"><span style="font-family: Arial"><span lang="EN-US">(4) Special ship power plants</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 18pt"><span style="font-size: larger"><span style="font-family: Arial"><b><span lang="EN-US">Core Classes</span>: </b><span lang="EN-US">Chinese Language, Advanced Engineering Thermodynamics, Mathematical Methods in Physics, Modern Measurement Technologies, Specialty Literature Reading, Advanced Fluid Mechanics, </span><span lang="EN-US" style="letter-spacing: -0.15pt">Automatic Control Theory, </span><span lang="EN-US">Analysis of Mechanical Vibration, Modern Marine Engineering, Analysis of Engineering Cycle, Numerical Computational Methods, Advanced Gas Dynamics, Linear System Dynamics, Simulation of Power Machinery System, Analysis of Power Machinery Performance, Finite Element Analysis for Engineering Structure, Alignment of Marine Shafting, Numerical Computation of Power Plant Vibration, Technology of Active Vibration Control, Practice of computational hydromechanics, Engineering Optimum Design, Transient Measurement of Gas Parameters, Special Engines, Multivariable Control, Fuzzy Control &amp; Its Application to Power Machinery, Control System Numeral Simulation, Application Technology of Computer, Marine Engines &amp; Propulsion System, Tensor Analysis</span></span></span></p>', NULL, 76, 1, ''),
