(346, 1, 'hrbeu', 40, 'Bachelor in Electronics Science and Technology', '2009-05-02 06:51:07', '2009-05-02 06:51:07', 'hrbeu', 'Bachelor in Electronics Science and Technology', 'Bachelor in Electronics Science and Technology', '<div class="Section1" style="layout-grid:  15.6pt none">\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-size: x-small"><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-weight: 700">Introduction: </span><span lang="EN-US">Electronic science and technology includes physical electronics, optoelectronics and microelectronics and technology, and so on. It is a comprehensive discipline combining electronics and information science. The Program is committed to cultivate senior professionals who grasp basis of theory, practical ability and professional knowledge of electronic science and technology and can work in the fields of optoelectronics, physical electronics and microelectronics. </span>This Program is also open for international students.</span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-size: x-small"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-weight: 700">Graduates'' career prospects: </span><span lang="EN-US">Because the subject of Electronic Science and Technology has almost covered every walk of life, there are great demands for the graduates. The graduates can take occupations in many aspects. They can do design, research, development and management in the field of electronic science and technology in research institutes, manufacturing enterprises, and universities and colleges. </span></span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-size: x-small"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-weight: 700">Core classes: </span><span lang="EN-US">electronic circuit, analog electronic technique, principle of microcomputer, electrodynamics, solid physics, semiconductor physics, theory of photic transmission, laser and infrared technology and photoelectric inspect technology, etc.</span></span></p>\r\n</div>', NULL, 109, 1, ''),
(347, 1, 'hrbeu', 40, 'Bachelor in Information and Computer Science', '2009-05-02 06:51:41', '2009-05-02 06:51:41', 'hrbeu', 'Bachelor in Information and Computer Science', 'Bachelor in Information and Computer Science', '<div class="Section1" style="layout-grid:  15.6pt none">\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-size: x-small"><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-weight: 700">Introduction: </span><span lang="EN-US">We are committed to cultivate senior engineering professionals who grasp fundamental theories and methods of information science and computer science, have accepted primary training in scientific research, and can solve practical problems. The Program mainly introduces fundamental knowledge, and basic methods of information science and computer science. </span>This Program is also open for international students.</span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-size: x-small"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-weight: 700">Course distinctions: </span><span lang="EN-US">On the one hand the Program has traditional mathematical curriculum, on the other hand the curriculum of mathematical model has already been added for training students to solve practical problems in various aspects of society. In addition, the Program pays attention to the ability of using computers and has corresponding courses. When students do graduation projects, they are encouraged to apply mathematical model and computer software.</span></span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-size: x-small"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-weight: 700">Graduates'' career prospects: </span><span lang="EN-US">The graduates can take occupations in many aspects. They can do teaching and research in universities, colleges and research institutes, or do research and the development of computer software.</span></span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-size: x-small"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-weight: 700">Core classes: </span><span lang="EN-US">mathematical analysis, advanced mathematics, complex variables functions, functions of real variable, basis of information science, modern algebra, coding theory, computational method, discrete mathematics, algorithmic language, digital computation software, database, computer graphics, probability theory, ordinary differential equations, partial differential equation, etc.</span></span></p>\r\n</div>', NULL, 101, 1, ''),
(348, 1, 'hrbeu', 40, 'Bachelor in Mathematics and Applied Mathematics', '2009-05-02 06:52:16', '2009-05-02 06:52:16', 'hrbeu', 'Bachelor in Mathematics and Applied Mathematics', 'Bachelor in Mathematics and Applied Mathematics', '<div class="Section1" style="layout-grid:  15.6pt none">\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-size: x-small"><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-weight: 700">Introduction: </span><span lang="EN-US">We are committed to cultivate senior engineering professionals, who have solid basis of mathematical theory and broad knowledge of mathematical model and computer. The Program not only borrows the traditional mathematical curriculum, but also has added curriculum of mathematical model to train students to solve practical problems solving. This curriculum bridges the practical problems with mathematical theory, and develops the insight of analyzing practical problems and innovation ability of solving problems. In addition, in order to improve adaptability of career selection and broaden the knowledge of students, this Program has many electives such as principle of computer and control theory and so on. </span>This Program is also open for international students.</span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-size: x-small"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-weight: 700">Graduates'' career prospects: </span><span lang="EN-US">The graduates can work at mathematical teaching and research in universities, colleges and research institutes, or work at mathematical applications and the development of computer software in enterprises, government services and departments of national defense.</span></span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-size: x-small"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-weight: 700">Core classes: </span><span lang="EN-US">mathematical analysis, advanced mathematics, dimensional analytic geometry, complex variables functions, functions of real variable and functional analysis, probability theory, mathematical statistics, ordinary differential equations, partial differential equation, computational method, operational research (including planning and graph theory), discrete mathematics and mathematical model, etc.</span></span></p>\r\n</div>', NULL, 91, 1, ''),
(349, 1, 'hrbeu', 40, 'Master in Optical Engineering', '2009-05-02 06:52:55', '2009-05-02 06:52:55', 'hrbeu', 'Master in Optical Engineering', 'Master in Optical Engineering', '<div class="Section1" style="layout-grid:  15.6pt none">\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-size: x-small"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-weight: 700">Introduction: </span><span lang="EN-US">Though the MEng Program was established in 1996, within a short period, it become one of the main teaching and researching bases of China, and is one of the best research base on fiber technology in North-east China. The faculty unit enjoys several national defense pre-research funds and other funds. Simultaneously the faculty unit bears the responsibility of cultivating high-level intellects and teaching and research in fiber technology. 5 projects of national and ministry level and 2 projects of industry sectors are undertaken, and several breakthroughs have been achieved in these years. Over 300 papers are published in important journals and conferences such as Electrical Journal, Communication Journal, Optical Journal and Acoustics Journal, etc. 200 papers have been cited by SCI</span>,<span lang="EN-US"> EI</span>,<span lang="EN-US"> ISTP. 2 academic books had been published and a research group has come into being. Labs for teaching and researching are: Fiber and sensor lab. </span>The classes of this Program can be lectured in English.</span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-size: x-small"><b><span lang="EN-US">Research Fields</span>:</b></span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-size: x-small"><span lang="EN-US">(1)<span style="color: black"> Fiber Optic Sensor, Transmission and Inform</span>ation Processing Technology</span></span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-size: x-small"><span lang="EN-US">(2)Application of Optical Information Technology in Communication and Microcomputer</span></span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-size: x-small"><b><span lang="EN-US">Core classes</span>: </b><span lang="EN-US">Chinese language, stochastic processes, advanced physical optics, measure, detection and sensing technology, interface and signal processing of fiber sensor, fiber communication theory, interferential fiber sensing technology, light wave guide<span style="color: red"> </span>theory, modern digital modulation and demodulation technology, modern fiber communication technology generality, queue theory, principle and design of fiber LAN, modern signal processing, digital image processing, design of advanced MCU, design of communication software, interferential fiber sensor, image transmission</span></span></p>\r\n</div>', NULL, 107, 1, ''),
