(392, 2, 'Wang Kunyan', 47, 'Graduation Ceremony, Degree Awarding Ceremony ', '2009-05-09 00:05:20', '2009-05-09 00:05:20', 'Gongxue Weekly', 'HEU Held Graduation Ceremony and Degree Awarding Ceremony for 2009 Graduate Students', 'HEU Held Graduation Ceremony and Degree Awarding Ceremony for 2009 Graduate Students', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 24pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: black; line-height: 170%">On April 1, HEU held Graduation Ceremony and Degree Awarding Ceremony for 2009 Graduate Students in Multi-functional Hall in Qihang Activity Center.</span><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: black; line-height: 170%">　</span></div>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 24pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: black; line-height: 170%"><img height="402" width="600" alt="" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/09/2009-05-09-93554.jpg" /></span></div>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 24pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: black; line-height: 170%">Prof. Yang Desen, vice president and dean of Graduate School, hosted the ceremony. Prof. Liu Zhigang, president and chairman of degree accreditation association, Prof. Qiu Changhua, vice chairman of degree accreditation association, Prof. Yang Shie, academician, and the other HEU officers including Prof. Gao Wanxin, Prof. Wei Lin, Prof. Bi Zhihua, Prof. Zhang Wenping and Prof Wu Qingwen, president assistant attended the ceremony and awarde3d degree certificates for the graduate students.</span></div>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 24pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 170%">46 students were awarded with PhD degrees, 1,280 students awarded with master degrees including one Pakistan student.</span><span style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 170%">　</span><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: black; line-height: 170%">On the ceremony, excellent PhD and master degree thesis were commended and awarded with prizes.</span></div>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 24pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: black; line-height: 170%"><img height="402" width="600" alt="" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/09/2009-05-09-17347.jpg" /></span></div>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 24pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: black; line-height: 170%">Mr. Liang Xiao, representative of 2009 graduate students, expressed his appreciation and passion to the university. He was committed to strengthen belief, to be innovative, to make progress, to scale new heights</span><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: black; line-height: 170%">，</span><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: black; line-height: 170%">and to draw a splendid life panorama with the knowledge and wits acquired from Alma Mater.</span></div>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 24pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: black; line-height: 170%">Prof. Sun Feng, PhD candidate advisor of Automation College, expressed his sincere congratulations and keen anticipation. He hoped the students may contributed the society, the people, the construction and development of Alma Mater.</span></div>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 24pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: black; line-height: 170%">In the end, Prof. Zhigang Liu delivered a speech to express his congratulations to the students, and appreciation to the advisors. He also gave suggestions to the students for their future development: 1) to be ambitious and to be committed to serve the people and the society.2) to be hard-working, down-to-earth, and innovative. 3) to study for all the time, to enhance cultivation both inside and outside.</span></div>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 24pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: black; line-height: 170%"><img height="399" width="600" alt="" src="/userfiles/image/2009/05/09/2009-05-09-38006.jpg" /></span></div>', NULL, 181, 1, ''),
