(404, 1, 'carol', 47, 'HEU Officially Signed the Contract to Host ACM-ICPC 2010', '2009-06-16 08:14:25', '2009-06-16 08:14:25', 'hrbeu', 'HEU Officially Signed the Contract to Host ACM-ICPC 2010', 'Within 18 to 22 April, Prof. Desen Yang, HEU vice president led HEU delegation observed the World Finals of ACM-ICPC 2009 and officially signed the contract to host the World Finals of ACM-ICPC 2010.', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 21pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt">Within 18 to 22 April, Prof. Desen Yang, HEU vice president led HEU delegation observed the World Finals of ACM-ICPC 2009 and officially signed the contract to host the World Finals of ACM-ICPC 2010. </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt"><font face="Times New Roman"><o:p></o:p></font></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 21pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-language: EN-US">Signing the contract marks the overall starting of the preparation progress. ACM steering committee will send one delegation to prepare the world final scheme with HEU team in June.</span></span></span><font face="Times New Roman"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 21pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-language: EN-US">The ACM (Association for Computing Machinery) International Collegiate Programming Contest (ICPC) traces its roots to a competition held at Texas A&amp;M in 1970 hosted by the Alpha Chapter of the UPE Computer Science Honor Society. The idea quickly gained popularity within the </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-language: EN-US"><font face="Times New Roman"><st1:country-region w:st="on"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma">United States</span></span></st1:country-region><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"> and </span></span><st1:country-region w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma">Canada</span></span></st1:place></st1:country-region><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"> as an innovative initiative to assist in the development of top students in the emerging field of computer science. The contest evolved into a multi-tier competition with the first Finals held at the ACM Computer Science Conference in 1977. Headquartered at </span></span><st1:place w:st="on"><st1:placename w:st="on"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma">Baylor</span></span></st1:placename><st1:placetype w:st="on"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma">University</span></span></st1:placetype></st1:place><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"> since the 1980s, the contest has expanded into a global network of universities hosting regional competitions that advance teams to the World Finals. Since IBM began its sponsorship of the ACM-ICPC World Finals in 1997, the contest has increased by a factor of 7.5. Participation has grown to involve several tens of thousands of the finest students and faculty in computing disciplines at 1,756 universities from 82 countries on six continents. </span></span><o:p></o:p></font></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 21pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-language: EN-US">The contest fosters creativity, teamwork, and innovation in building new software programs, and enables students to test their ability to perform under pressure. Quite simply, it is the oldest, largest, and most prestigious programming contest in the world. </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-language: EN-US"><font face="Times New Roman"><o:p></o:p></font></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 21pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-language: EN-US">ACM, </span></span></span><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-language: EN-US"><a href="http://www.acm.org/" target="new"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="color: windowtext; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none">the Association for Computing Machinery</span></span></a></span></span><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-language: EN-US">, is an educational and scientific society uniting the world''s computing educators, researchers and professionals to inspire dialogue, share resources and address the field''s challenges. ACM strengthens the profession''s collective voice through strong leadership, promotion of the highest standards, and recognition of technical excellence. ACM supports the professional growth of its members by providing opportunities for life-long learning, career development, and professional networking.</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 21pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt">100 teams won the places for the world finals from 7109 teams, from 1,838 universities, from 88 countries/regions, from 6 continents. The scale of the contest is increase annually.</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt"><font face="Times New Roman"><o:p></o:p></font></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 21pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt">During the trip, HEU delegation gave presentation on preparation. The delegation observed the venue, accommodation, catering, transportation, and organization of ACM-ICPC 2009. The delegation consulted 2009 OC on live show, volunteer work, site service and so on. The tour helps HEU to accumulate experience for HEU hosting the World Finals 2010. As the honorary guest, Prof. Desen Yang award prizes for the winners in the closing ceremony.</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt"><font face="Times New Roman"><o:p></o:p></font></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify">&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1012, 1, ''),
(405, 1, 'carol', 47, 'Prof. Lin Wei Made a Presentation in Sunshine Forum', '2009-06-16 08:15:04', '2009-06-16 08:19:23', 'hrbeu', 'Prof. Lin Wei Made a Presentation in Sunshine Forum', 'Prof. Lin Wei, HEU vice president, made a presentation titled of “2008: The Waves of China Surged Forward Dramatically” in the 452nd Sunshine Forum on 14 March.', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 21pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt">Prof. Lin Wei, HEU vice president, made a presentation titled of &ldquo;2008: The Waves of China Surged Forward Dramatically&rdquo; in the 452<sup>nd</sup> Sunshine Forum on 14 March.</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt"><font size="3"><font face="Times New Roman"><o:p></o:p></font></font></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 21pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt">The presentation elaborated mainly on three issues: 1) financial crisis swept across the world, and how should Chinese government deal with the crisis? 2) Obama presided Pentagon, and how Sino-US relationship develops? 3) Democratic Party was defeated badly and how should the exchanges across the straits?<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>After the presentation, Prof. Wei answered the questions from the students and his sharp views won applauds from the audience.</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt"><font size="3"><font face="Times New Roman"><o:p></o:p></font></font></span></p>', NULL, 884, 1, ''),
(406, 1, 'carol', 47, 'Electrical Engineering & Electronic Teaching Center Constructed a Multi-functional Antenna Tower for Cross Ocean Communication', '2009-06-16 08:16:01', '2009-06-16 08:19:03', 'hrbeu', 'Electrical Engineering & Electronic Teaching Center Constructed a Multi-functional Antenna Tower for Cross Ocean Communication', 'The Four-wave-band Rotatable Yagi Antenna Tower was constructed successfully, which is the first amateur wireless radio communication antenna tower for practice teaching at HEU and can realize cross-ocean communication.', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 21pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt">The Four-wave-band Rotatable Yagi Antenna Tower was constructed successfully, which is the first amateur wireless radio communication antenna tower for practice teaching at HEU and can realize cross-ocean communication. The antenna tower is ranking among the top universities in </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt"><font face="Times New Roman"><font size="3"><st1:country-region w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma">China</span></span></st1:place></st1:country-region><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma">.</span></span><o:p></o:p></font></font></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 21pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt">Since 2008 Electrical Engineering and </span></span></span><font size="3"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt"><font face="Times New Roman"><st1:place w:st="on"><st1:placename w:st="on"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma">Electronic</span></span></st1:placename><st1:placename w:st="on"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma">Teaching</span></span></st1:placename><st1:placetype w:st="on"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma">Center</span></span></st1:placetype></st1:place><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"> opened &ldquo;Amateur Wireless Radio Communication (Amateur Radio Station) Course&rdquo;as one chain specialty practice course for freshmen and sophomore students. The Center spent 3 months to develop the </span></span><st1:place w:st="on"><st1:placename w:st="on"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma">Antenna</span></span></st1:placename><st1:placetype w:st="on"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma">Tower</span></span></st1:placetype></st1:place></font></span><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt"> which has now been applied to experimental teaching. The course now can use amateur community radio frequency of 7MHz</span><span style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''">、</span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt">14MHz for normal practice teaching and can also be used for distance DX cross ocean communication practice.</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt"><font face="Times New Roman"><o:p></o:p></font></span></font></p>', NULL, 885, 1, ''),
(407, 1, 'carol', 47, 'ACM/ICPC Executive Director Inspected at HEU', '2009-06-16 08:16:49', '2009-06-16 08:16:49', 'hrbeu', 'ACM/ICPC Executive Director Inspected at HEU', 'On March 16, Prof. William B. Poucher, ACM/ICPC Executive Director, led a delegation to inspect HEU.', '<p class="MsoNormal" align="left" style="text-align: left; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 21pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt">On March 16, Prof. William B. Poucher, ACM/ICPC Executive Director, led a delegation to inspect HEU.</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt"><font size="3"><font face="Times New Roman"><o:p></o:p></font></font></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" align="left" style="text-align: left; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 21pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt">Mr. Du Yuxin, secretary of municipal Party committee, and standing member of provincial Party committee, met with the delegation led by Prof. Poucher. Prof. Liu Zhigang, HEU president, and Prof. Yang Desen, HEU vice president, attended the meeting. </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt"><font size="3"><font face="Times New Roman"><o:p></o:p></font></font></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" align="left" style="text-align: left; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 21pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt">Prof. Poucher expressed that he was very pleased to visit </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt"><font size="3"><font face="Times New Roman"><st1:city w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma">Harbin</span></span></st1:place></st1:city><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"> and HEU again. He also noted that, the 34th ACM/ICPC World Finals is going to be held at HEU in 2010, when the programming design &eacute;lites from over 100 universities are going to be gathering at HEU. He anticipated to witness the occasion at HEU sooner. In the opinion of Prof. Poucher, ACM/ICPC is depending on the communities. With the effort of the community we can obtain success, create excellence and explore a beautiful future.</span></span><o:p></o:p></font></font></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" align="left" style="text-align: left; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 21pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt">Mr. Du Yuxin expressed his admiration for the efforts delivered by Prof. Poucher. Mr. Du felt the honor to participate into the event and to share the achievement of ACM/ICPC. Mr. Du promised, on behalf of the municipal Party committee and the municipal government, he will support the Contest in cooperation.</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt"><font size="3"><font face="Times New Roman"><o:p></o:p></font></font></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 919, 1, ''),
(408, 1, 'carol', 47, 'Mr. Du Yuxin, Secretary of Municipal Party Committee, and Standing Member of Provincial Party Committee, Inspected HEU', '2009-06-16 08:17:21', '2009-06-16 08:17:39', 'hrbeu', 'Mr. Du Yuxin, Secretary of Municipal Party Committee, and Standing Member of Provincial Party Committee, Inspected HEU', 'Mr. Du Yuxin, secretary of municipal Party committee, and standing member of provincial Party committee, Mr. Nie Yunling, secretary-general of municipal Party committee, Ms. Wang Li, deputy mayor inspected HEU on 16 March.', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 21pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt">Mr. Du Yuxin, secretary of municipal Party committee, and standing member of provincial Party committee, Mr. Nie Yunling, secretary-general of municipal Party committee, Ms. Wang Li, deputy mayor inspected HEU on 16 March.</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt"><font size="3"><font face="Times New Roman"><o:p></o:p></font></font></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 21pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt">Prof. Liu Zhigang, HEU president made a presentation on HEU development for the officers from the municipal government. HEU board members attended the meeting. </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt"><font size="3"><font face="Times New Roman"><o:p></o:p></font></font></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 21pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt">Prof. Liu Zhigang made a presentation on HEU development. He noted that HEU was facing the opportunity of revitalizing </span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt"><font size="3"><font face="Times New Roman"><st1:place w:st="on"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma">Northeast China</span></span></st1:place><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma">, enhancing national competence through shipbuilding, developing nuclear and power in priority, and exploring ocean resources. In the supports from the provincial Party committee, provincial government, municipal Party committee, and municipal government, HEU stepped into the stage of development in the highest-speed, bounty achievement, and prominent improvement in school-running in HEU history. In the development progress, HEU is committed to improve the contribution efficiency towards developing domestic economy.</span></span><o:p></o:p></font></font></span></p>', NULL, 172, 1, ''),
(409, 1, 'carol', 47, '2008 HEU Excellent PhD Thesis List was Announced', '2009-06-16 08:18:16', '2009-06-16 08:18:16', 'hrbeu', '2008 HEU Excellent PhD Thesis List was Announced', '2008 HEU Excellent PhD Thesis List was announced and 10 graduate students won the honor.', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 20pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt">2008 HEU Excellent PhD Thesis List was announced and 10 graduate students won the honor.</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt"><font size="3"><font face="Times New Roman"><o:p></o:p></font></font></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 20pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt">25 PhDs and 68 masters applied to the competition. After the experts&rsquo; appraisal, 10 PhD theses and 30 master theses came to the fore. HEU awarded prizes to the 10 PhD winners and their advisors.</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt"><font size="3"><font face="Times New Roman"><o:p></o:p></font></font></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 20pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Tahoma"><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt">The University will recommend 5 theses to 2009 National Excellent PhD Thesis Competition.</span></span></span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 150%; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.5pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt"><font size="3"><font face="Times New Roman"><o:p></o:p></font></font></span></p>', NULL, 126, 1, ''),
(410, 2, 'FAO', 47, '', '2009-06-29 17:43:04', '2009-06-29 17:43:04', 'FAO', 'Graduates Bid Farewell to Alma Mater', 'Graduates Bid Farewell to Alma Mater', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="left" vspace="0" hspace="0">\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign="top" align="left" style="border-right: #f3f5f7; padding-right: 9pt; border-top: #f3f5f7; padding-left: 9pt; padding-bottom: 0cm; border-left: #f3f5f7; padding-top: 0cm; border-bottom: #f3f5f7; background-color: transparent">\r\n            <div style="text-indent: 20pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 170%">2009 graduates will bid farewell to Alma Mater and start new journey. The colleges/departments will consistently hold graduation ceremony within 29 and 30. HEU officers will seperately attend graduation ceremonies of the colleges/departments and award diplomas and degrees.</span></div>\r\n            <div style="text-indent: 20pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 170%">Over 3, 300 HEU graduate students and over 700 postgraduate students completed their study at HEU successfully. HEU specially established steering committee to instruct and serve student departure affairs. The related departments established on-site office to help graduates go through the departure procedure. </span></div>\r\n            <div style="text-indent: 20pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 170%">HEU Student Culture Cultivation Base hosted </span>Electro-acoustic Band<span style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 170%"> Show and Graduation Party for the graduate students.</span></div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>', NULL, 91, 1, ''),
(411, 2, 'FAO', 47, '', '2009-06-29 17:44:29', '2009-06-29 17:44:29', 'FAO', 'Governor Zhanshu Li Inspected HEU', 'Governor Zhanshu Li Inspected HEU', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 20pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 170%">On June 26, Governor Zhanshu Li, Vice Governor Youdong Cheng led the directors of nine provincial department inspected HEU. During the inspection, the delegation performed research on the issues of how universities quickening S&amp;T results industrialization and providing supports on talent and intellectual aspects for local economy development. </span></div>\r\n<div style="line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 170%">The delegation inspected HEU nuclear simulation center lab, comprehensive simulation lab, and dynamic positioning lab. They watched the presentations lab profile, on-going research projects and achievement. The delegation also exchanged views on S&amp;T, technology development and academic exchanges. </span></div>\r\n<div style="text-justify: inter-ideograph; line-height: 170%"><span style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 170%">The delegation toured around HEU S&amp;T Achievement Exhibition on Energy, Material and Electromechanics. They hoped the results can be industrialized and serve the societ6y in an early day.</span></div>\r\n<div style="text-justify: inter-ideograph; line-height: 170%"><span style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 170%">During inspect in Collegiate Students Entrepreneurship Alliance, governor talked with student entrepreneur Tianxiang Guo and expressed admiration to Guo. Guo presented his book as a gift to governor. HEU student gave mug with on-site shot pictures to governor. </span></div>\r\n<div style="line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 170%">When inspecting HEU graduate employment work, governor carefully watched the presentation on year 2004 to 2008 HEU graduate student one-time employment and year 2009 HEU graduate employment exhibition board, governor pointed that the analysis on 100% employment department diagram will help us grab the information of popular industries and popular majors development trends and provided guidance for discipline adjustment.</span></div>\r\n<div style="line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 170%">After the site visits, governor listed to the report presented by HEU staff. In the presentation by Prof. Zhigang Liu, HEU president, he introduced HEU profile and HEU advantages. In the progress of quickening development speed, HEU taking the goal of enhancing the contributing role, following implementing the strategy of revitalize the province through science and education, displaying the advantages of manpower and technology, give priority to satisfying provincial demands in the aspects of discipline arrangement, student recruitment, talent supply, industrial exploration and S&amp;T product transfer. Under the auspice of the provincial government, HEU entered into the stage of rapid development, increasing achievements, and upgrading school running level. HEU will appreciate the concerns and supports from the provincial government, combine own advantages and regional economy development demands, upgrade school running level and quality, and consistently contribute the goal of developing provincial economy.</span></div>\r\n<div style="line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 170%">In governor&rsquo;s address, he concluded that HEU was a distinctive university and the university was demonstrating a booming development trend. He hoped HEU can obtain greater achievement during the progress of building high-level research university.</span></div>', NULL, 84, 1, ''),
(412, 2, 'FAO', 47, 'FAO', '2009-06-29 17:47:53', '2009-06-29 17:53:00', 'China National Opera', 'China National Opera House Performed at HEU', '', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style="text-justify: inter-ideograph; line-height: 170%"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 170%">On June 20, China National Opera House struck up grand and splendid musical works. Ministry of Education, Ministry of Culture and Ministry of Finance hosted 2009 High Art Entering into Campuses Series Performance in North-east Universities of China. </span></div>\r\n<div style="line-height: 150%"><span style="line-height: 150%">At the beginning of the performance, Prof. Desen Yang, HEU vice president expressed appreciation to the artists and delivered congratulations forehand.</span></div>\r\n<div style="line-height: 150%"><span style="line-height: 150%">In the spirit of &ldquo;sing live, play live, conduct live and speak the truth&rdquo;,&nbsp;over 130 artists from the Opera Troupe, Chorus, and Symphony Orchestra of National Opera House played &nbsp;selected pieces from Carmen, La dame aux Cam&eacute;lias, and Turandot. The concert adopted a way of combining acting and lecturing, and presented vivid description on the art connotations. The concert was presented solo, duet, and choir in Italian and French. </span></div>\r\n<div style="line-height: 150%"><span style="line-height: 150%">Over 2000 HEU staff and students attended the concert and was impressed by the splendid performance. <img height="600" width="402" alt="" src="/userfiles/image/2009/06/29/2009-06-29-82448.jpg" /></span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 5pt; font-family: ˎ̥; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-bidi-font-family: 宋体; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN"><v:shapetype id="_x0000_t75" stroked="f" filled="f" path="m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe" o:preferrelative="t" o:spt="75" coordsize="21600,21600"><font face="宋体, MS Song"><v:stroke joinstyle="miter"><