:shape></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 117, 1, '/userfiles/image/2009/06/29/2009-06-29-82448.jpg'),
(413, 2, 'FAO', 47, '', '2009-06-30 09:33:12', '2009-06-30 09:33:45', 'FAO', 'HEU Officers Visited the Candidate for ROBOCON National Preliminary Round', 'HEU Officers Visited the Candidate for ROBOCON National Preliminary Round', '<p><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 10pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: EN-US">On June 23, HEU officers including Mr. Huanmin Gu, Prof. Zhignag Liu, and Prof Lin Wei visited the Robot Innovation Workshop student candidates who are going to participate into the national preliminary round of the 8<sup>th </sup></span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 10.5pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">ROBOCON, ABU Asia-Pacific <span style="color: black">Robot</span> Contest.</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 10pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: EN-US"> </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 10pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: EN-US"><img height="335" alt="" width="500" src="/userfiles/image/2009/06/30/2009-06-30-25161.jpg" /></span></p>', NULL, 98, 1, '/userfiles/image/2009/06/30/2009-06-30-25161.jpg'),
(414, 2, 'FAO', 47, '', '2009-06-30 10:11:29', '2009-06-30 10:11:29', 'FAO', 'THE FINAL SHOW：2009 Graduate Party Presented a Splendid Night', 'THE FINAL SHOW：2009 Graduate Party Presented a Splendid Night', '<p><span style="line-height: 170%">On June 26, hosted by National Collegiate Student Cultivation Educational Base, the Final Show for 2009 graduate students was on. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="line-height: 170%">The performance started from passionate hot dance. Haizhiyun Choir sang &ldquo;Country Road&rdquo;, &ldquo;Childhood&rdquo;, and &ldquo;The Summer Blew by the Wind&rdquo;. The songs recalled the memory for the past four years. The songs of Never Leave Me cherished friendship. Facing the coming departure, the actors and the audience expressed their reluctance to bid farewell. Poetry recitals- I graduated and Once again, Walk Around the Campus, touched the audience emotions.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt">Accompanying the song &ldquo;Blessing&rdquo;, the Party came to the end. &nbsp;The Announcers sent their best wishes to all the graduate students.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt"><img height="400" width="600" alt="" src="/userfiles/image/2009/06/30/2009-06-30-85662.jpg" /></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt"><img height="400" width="600" alt="" src="/userfiles/image/2009/06/30/2009-06-30-44231.jpg" /></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt"><img height="400" width="600" alt="" src="/userfiles/image/2009/06/30/2009-06-30-38926.jpg" /></span></span></p>', NULL, 120, 1, '/userfiles/image/2009/06/30/2009-06-30-38926.jpg'),
(415, 2, 'FAO', 47, '', '2009-07-06 23:24:00', '2009-07-06 23:24:00', 'FAO', 'HEU Won Outstanding Achievement in ACM/ICPC China •the 3rd Northeast Regional Collegiate Student Programming Contest', 'HEU Won Outstanding Achievement in ACM/ICPC China •the 3rd Northeast Regional Collegiate Student Programming Contest', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 21pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span style="line-height: 170%">ACM/ICPC China &middot;the 3<sup>rd</sup> Northeast Regional Collegiate Student Programming Contest concluded at Dalian University of Technology in June 27 and 28. 11 teams won the first class awards and HEU won four of the eleven. HEU top all the attending universities.</span></span></span></div>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 21pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span style="line-height: 170%">117 teams from 49 universities in Heilongjiang Province, Jilin Province, Liaoning Province, and Inner Mongolia Province participated into the contest. The 117 teams were selected through provincial contests. HEU had totally 5 teams participated. </span></span></span></div>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 21pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span style="line-height: 170%">HEU Team 1 completed 6 problems of the total 9 problems and was ranked the 2<sup>nd</sup> among the 117 teams. The performance toped all the Heilongjiang teams in the competition.</span></span></span></div>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 21pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span style="line-height: 170%"><img height="412" width="600" alt="" src="/userfiles/image/2009/07/06/2009-07-06-33478.jpg" /></span></span></span></div>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ACM International Collegiate Programming Contest (abbreviated as ACM-ICPC or just ICPC) is an annual multi-tiered computer programming competition among the universities of the world. The contest is sponsored by </span></span><span style="font-size: 10.5pt"><span style="font-size: small"><a title="IBM" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IBM"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span style="color: windowtext; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none">IBM</span></span></a><span style="font-family: Times New Roman">. Headquartered at </span></span><span style="font-size: small"><a title="Baylor University" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baylor_University"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span style="color: windowtext; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none">Baylor University</span></span></a><span style="font-family: Times New Roman">, with autonomous regions on six continents, the ICPC is directed by Baylor Professor William B. Poucher, Executive Director, and operates under the auspices of the </span></span><span style="font-size: small"><a title="Association for Computing Machinery" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Association_for_Computing_Machinery"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span style="color: windowtext; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none">Association for Computing Machinery</span></span></a><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"> (ACM). The 2009 ACM-ICPC World Finals were held in Stockholm, Sweden, April 18-22, at the Grand Hotel of Sweden, the Radisson Strand, and the Diplomat Hotel. The World Finals was hosted by KTH - The Royal Institute of Technology. There were 100 teams from over 200 regional sites to competing for the World Championship. The </span></span><span style="font-size: small"><a title="St. Petersburg Institute of Fine Mechanics and Optics" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/St._Petersburg_Institute_of_Fine_Mechanics_and_Optics"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span style="color: windowtext; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none">St. Petersburg Institute of Fine Mechanics and Optics</span></span></a><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"> defended their championship title to win their third world championship. </span></span><span style="font-size: small"><a title="Tsinghua University" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tsinghua_University"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span style="color: windowtext; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none">Tsinghua University</span></span></a><span style="font-family: Times New Roman">, </span></span><span style="font-size: small"><a title="St. Petersburg State University" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/St._Petersburg_State_University"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span style="color: windowtext; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none">St. Petersburg State University</span></span></a><span style="font-family: Times New Roman">, and </span></span></span><span style="font-size: small"><a title="Saratov State University" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saratov_State_University"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><span style="color: windowtext; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none">Saratov State University</span></span></a><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"> also received gold medals. HEU was awarded the right to host 2010 World Finals in 2009. Now HEU is preparing for the World Finals under the supervision of the ACM ICPC committee.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: small"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman"><img height="376" width="600" alt="" src="/userfiles/image/2009/07/06/2009-07-06-81378.jpg" /></span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 119, 1, '/userfiles/image/2009/07/06/2009-07-06-33478.jpg'),
(416, 2, 'FAO', 47, 'HEU Was Officially Awarded with EMBA Education Recruitment Qualification', '2009-07-06 23:25:15', '2009-07-06 23:25:15', 'FAO', 'HEU Was Officially Awarded with EMBA Education Recruitment Qualification', 'HEU Was Officially Awarded with EMBA Education Recruitment Qualification', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 21pt; line-height: 150%"><span style="line-height: 150%">Approved by Degree Committee Office of State Council, HEU was listed into the professional degree cultivation institution for the 2<sup>nd </sup>Batch of National Executive Master of Business Administration Programs (EMBA) , which marks significant progress achieved by HEU MBA education.</span></div>\r\n<div style="text-justify: inter-ideograph; text-indent: 21pt; line-height: 150%"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 150%">Executive MBA (EMBA) programs developed to meet the educational needs of managers and executives, allowing students to earn an MBA or another business-related graduate degree in two years or less while working full time. Participants come from every type and size of organization &ndash; profit, nonprofit, government &mdash; representing a variety of industries. EMBA students typically have a higher level of work experience, often 10 years or more, compared to other MBA students. In response to the increasing number of EMBA programs offered, The Executive MBA Council was formed in 1981 to advance executive education. In recruiting aspect, universities enjoy broader independent recruiting power by independently organizing entry exams and admitting procedure. In 1997, approved by Degree Office of State Council, HEU officially develop MBA education programs. By exploration and practices in years, HEU is enhancing its faculty construction, and talent cultivation. HEU MBA brand image was enhanced, and social influence and recognition were also improved consistently. </span></div>\r\n<div style="text-justify: inter-ideograph; text-indent: 21pt; line-height: 150%"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 150%">Now there are 62 universities have EMBA recruiting power, and in Heilongjiang only HEU and HIT are qualified for EMBA recruitment.</span></div>', NULL, 91, 1, ''),
(417, 2, 'FAO', 47, '', '2009-07-06 23:27:08', '2009-07-06 23:27:08', 'FAO', 'The Delegation of the 21st  Century Korea-China Exchange Association Visited HEU', 'The Delegation of the 21st  Century Korea-China Exchange Association Visited HEU\r\nHEU Signed Cooperative Agreement with Seoul Cyber University\r\n', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 21pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="line-height: 170%">On July 1<sup>st</sup>, the delegation of the 21<sup>st</sup> Century Korea-China Exchange Association and Seoul Cyber University Student Delegation visited HEU. HEU signed cooperative agreement with Seoul Cyber University.</span></div>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 21pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="line-height: 170%">Prof. Zhigang Liu, HEU president, and Prof. Wanxin Gao, vice president, met with the delegations. In the meeting, Prof. Liu expressed welcome to the delegations and briefed HEU profile. He also delivered appreciation to the distinctive contributions from Mr. Han Kyu Kim, director of the Association.</span></div>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 21pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="line-height: 170%">Prof. Liu expressed his pleasure to establish friendly relationship with Seoul Cyber University and hoped to initiate substantial progress for cooperation. He wished the two universities can promote the friendship between China and Korea. </span></div>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 21pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="line-height: 170%">The student representatives from the two universities held a meeting to enhance mutual understanding. </span></div>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 21pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="line-height: 170%">The members of the 21<sup>st</sup> Century Korea-China Exchange Association are all contributors to the friendship between ROK and China. The Association was dedicated to enhance friendship between the two countries through the exchange activities of celebrities of the two societies. Mr. Kim was appointed as guest professor of HEU and had visited HEU frequently. Mr. Kim was active in promoting HEU establishing cooperation networks with ROK universities.</span></div>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 21pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="line-height: 170%">Seoul</span><span style="line-height: 170%"> Cyber University was elected as &ldquo;the Most Distinctive Cyber University&rdquo; in the comprehensive appraisal by Korea HR Ministry. The University has 16 departments in 5 faculties, committed into cultivating global HR for internationalized age, cultivating the innovative talents leading knowledge information society, and cultivating the talents for the nation and the society. The university is dedicated to expand life-long educational opportunities beyond age and region.</span></div>\r\n<p><img height="402" width="600" alt="" src="/userfiles/image/2009/07/06/2009-07-06-29126.jpg" /></p>\r\n<p><img height="402" width="600" alt="" src="/userfiles/image/2009/07/06/2009-07-06-33041.jpg" /></p>', NULL, 105, 1, '/userfiles/image/2009/07/06/2009-07-06-33041.jpg');
