(431, 2, 'FAO', 47, 'Rate, Graduate Student, Post-graduate Examination', '2009-07-23 10:10:48', '2009-07-23 10:10:48', 'FAO', 'The Rate of HEU 2009 Graduate Student Taking Post-graduate Examination Being 43%: Breaking the Historical Record', 'The Rate of HEU 2009 Graduate Student Taking Post-graduate Examination Being 43%: Breaking the Historical Record', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style="line-height: 150%"><span style="line-height: 150%">Undergraduate student one-time employment rate was 93.6%, which saw a downturn of 3.29, and post-graduate student one-time employment rate 94.3%, which decreased 1.49 comparing to last year. However, the rate of HEU undergraduate student taking post-graduate examination was climbing to 43.25% from 36.55%.</span><span style="line-height: 170%">Additionally, this year the University has 14 undergraduate students volunteered to work in the most arduous region in Western China, 7 students are going to act volunteers in Western Youth Volunteer Service Base, 14 students were recruited into army, and 105 students will work in police system, which broke HEU record.</span></div>', NULL, 505, 1, ''),
(432, 2, 'FAO', 47, 'Confernce, Sports', '2009-07-23 10:55:29', '2009-07-23 10:56:59', 'FAO', 'Two HEU Teachers Attended the 25th World Universiade Summer Sports and Science Conference', 'Two HEU Teachers Attended the 25th World Universiade Summer Sports and Science Conference', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 21pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="line-height: 170%">The 25<sup>th</sup> World Universiade Summer Sports and Science Conference was held in Belgrade within 2 and 5 July. Peiyu Zhao and Di Feng of HEU Sports Faculty attended the conference and presented lecture in session.</span></div>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 21pt; line-height: 170%" align="left"><span style="line-height: 170%">The conference had attendance of over 130 scholars, professors, administrative staff in university sports discipline and students from 33 countries in 5 continents. The theme of the conference was </span><span style="line-height: 170%">&ldquo;The role of university sports in education and society&mdash;&mdash;A platform for change&rdquo;. The attendance agreed that sports was not only a educational method, but also a part of human right and human responsibilities, which had important influence on knowledge, economy, ecology crisis and social harmony. </span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 711, 1, ''),
(436, 3, 'Shining', 50, '', '2009-10-19 12:14:24', '2009-10-19 12:14:24', 'Web', 'About Harbin', '', '<p style="text-align: center">&nbsp;Harbin--------------------The beautiful city in Northeast China</p>\r\n<p><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><span style="color: black"><img height="141" width="142" alt="" src="/userfiles/image/2009/10/19/2009-10-19-36685.jpg" /></span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; color: black; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">Harbin</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; color: black; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"> is the capital of Heilongjiang Province of The People''s Republic of China. It is not only the center of politics, economy, transportation and culture in Northeast China, but also the biggest and second pop</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">ulous metropolis among <st1:country-region w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">China</st1:place></st1:country-region>''s provincial cities. It <span style="color: black">covers a total area of 53,068 square kilometers, with the urban area of 7,086 square kilometers and urban built-up area of 302.41 square kilometers. It enjoys a total population of 9.874 million and urban citizens of 4.755 million. It has 48 ethnic groups, minorities of which amount to 660,000 in population.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style="width: 381px; height: 339px" alt="" src="/userfiles/image/2009/10/19/2009-10-19-86712.jpg" /><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; color: black; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">Specific historical processes and geographical location have jointly created Harbin, a city with exotic beauty, which marries not only the history and culture of northern ethnic minorities, but also Chinese and foreign cultures. As a noted historical and cultural city and tourist city, it is</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"> </span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; color: black; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">reputed to </span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">be &ldquo;<st1:placename w:st="on">Ice</st1:placename> <st1:placetype w:st="on">City</st1:placetype> in the North &quot;, &ldquo;A Pearl on the Neck of the Swan&rdquo;, &ldquo;<st1:city w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">Mosc<span style="color: black">ow</span></st1:place></st1:city><span style="color: black"> in the East&rdquo;, &ldquo;Oriental Paris&rdquo; and</span> &ldquo;Summer <span style="color: black">Metropolis&rdquo;. In the year 2006, <st1:city w:st="on">Harbin</st1:city> made appearance on the list of &ldquo;Chinese Characteristic Charm City 200&rdquo;, and it is the only representative of <st1:country-region w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">China</st1:place></st1:country-region>''s bid for Winter Olympics! On July 16, 2008, the Olympic Flame arrived at the ice city.<br />\r\n</span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">As the city flower, lilac has made <st1:city w:st="on">Harbin</st1:city> noted as the <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:placename w:st="on">Lilac</st1:placename> <st1:placetype w:st="on">City</st1:placetype></st1:place>.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">Landmarks in <st1:city w:st="on">Harbin</st1:city> are the St. Sophia Church, the <st1:placename w:st="on">Dragon</st1:placename> <st1:placetype w:st="on">Tower</st1:placetype>, and the <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:placename w:st="on">Flood</st1:placename> <st1:placename w:st="on">Control</st1:placename> <st1:placetype w:st="on">Monument</st1:placetype></st1:place>.</span></p>', NULL, 69, 1, '/userfiles/image/2009/10/19/2009-10-19-86712.jpg'),
(437, 3, 'Shining', 51, '', '2009-10-19 13:43:08', '2009-10-19 13:43:08', 'HEU', 'About HEU', '', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style="text-justify: inter-ideograph"><span style="font-size: 13pt; color: black">Harbin Engineering University (HEU) sits at the scenic Songhua River in the ice city of Harbin in North China. It is among the first batch of &quot;211 Project&quot; universities that are entitled to enjoy first priority from the state in construction and development and also one of the universities that have Graduate School. Moreover, HEU is an important base for talent cultivation and scientific research in the fields of ship industry, ocean exploration and nuclear application.</span></div>\r\n<div style="text-justify: inter-ideograph"><span style="font-size: 13pt; color: black"><img height="279" width="518" alt="" src="/userfiles/image/2009/10/19/2009-10-19-33917.jpg" /></span></div>\r\n<div style="text-justify: inter-ideograph"><span style="font-size: 13pt; color: black">The predecessor of HEU is PLA Military Engineering Institute established in 1953 (abbr. HME). In 1970, in the former location, Harbin Ship Engineering Institute was founded by the entire crew of naval engineering department and some other cadre teachers of every </span><span style="font-size: 13pt; color: black">other department, and it was renamed Harbin Engineering University in 1994. HEU was selected as a national key university by the State Council in 1978, authorized by the State Council to award master and doctoral degrees in the first batch in 1982, selected as one of the first few &quot;211 Project&quot; universities to receive preferential support from the state in 1996, authorized by the Ministry of Education to have Graduate School in 2002</span><span style="font-size: 13pt; color: black">, and jointly </span><span style="font-size: 13pt; color: black">constructed by the Commission of Science and Technology for National Defense Industry</span><span style="font-size: 13pt; color: black">, the Ministry of Education, </span><span style="font-size: 13pt; color: black">Heilongjiang Provincial People''s Government</span><span style="font-size: 13pt; color: black"> a</span><span style="font-size: 13pt">nd the navy in 2007</span><span style="font-size: 13pt">. Cu<span style="color: black">rrently, HEU is subordinate to </span></span><span style="font-size: 13pt; color: black">the </span><span style="font-size: 13pt; color: black">Ministry of Industry and Information.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="font-size: 13pt">The floor area of HEU is 1.26 million square meters with a building area of 886 thousand square meters. The architecture of HEU embodies an imposingly exquisite combination of Chinese and Western elements, featuring flying eaves and jade tiles. The university comprises 17 colleges. And there are 2 departments and 1 center: foreign languages department, department of physical military training, and engineering training center. There are over 40 research institutes and over 150 special and basic laboratories, including 2 national key laboratories, 2 Defense key disciplines Labs, 2 Yin Zhi-level academic base for innovations, 2 national electric electronic teaching base, 3 National experimental teaching demonstration centers and 1 </span><span style="font-size: 13pt">National University Students Cultural Quality Education Base</span><span style="font-size: 13pt">.</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 13pt">In the course of over half a century, HEU has formed a well-structured discipline system that is characterized by a reasonable coordinated development of major disciplines in the fields of ship industry, ocean exploration and nuclear application together with related disciplines of other fields. Now there are 57 specialties for undergraduates, 94 specialties for Master candidates (MBA and MPA included), 22 for Master of Engineering fields, 6 for PhD subjects, 25 specialties for Doctoral candidates, 11 post-doctoral mobile stations, and 1 post-doctoral research station. The specialties cover 7 discipline groups and 37 first-class disciplines, with 3 national key disciplines, 7 national defense key disciplines, and 24 provincial and ministerial key disciplines.</span></p>', NULL, 37, 1, '/userfiles/image/2009/10/19/2009-10-19-33917.jpg'),
(438, 3, 'Shining', 52, '', '2009-10-19 13:45:22', '2009-10-19 13:45:22', 'Web', 'About Shangri-La Hotel Harbin', '', '<p><img style="width: 450px; height: 258px" alt="" src="/userfiles/image/2009/10/19/2009-10-19-31692.jpg" /></p>\r\n<p><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">Since the first appearance in <st1:country-region w:st="on">Singapore</st1:country-region> in 1971, Shangri-La Hotels have become the largest luxury hotel group in <st1:place w:st="on">Asia</st1:place>, and has been regarded as one of the world''s best hotel management groups.</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"> </span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">Shangri-La''s reputation comes from James Hilton''s legendary novel &ldquo;Lost Horizon&rdquo;, which depicts Shangri-La in details as a </span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">wonderland</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"> lying in the mountains and peaks of <st1:country-region w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">Tibet</st1:place></st1:country-region>. People who stay there experience unprecedented peace.</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"> Today, Shangri-La has become synonymous of the <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:placetype w:st="on">Land</st1:placetype> of <st1:placename w:st="on">Cockaigne</st1:placename></st1:place>. Shangri-La Hotel&rsquo;s excellent service and agreeable environment perfectly match the name which is filled with mystery.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><img style="width: 470px; height: 286px" alt="" src="/userfiles/image/2009/10/19/2009-10-19-85059.jpg" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">Harbin Shangri-La Hotel is an international five-star business hotel adjacent to the scenic south bank of the <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:placename w:st="on">Songhua</st1:placename> <st1:placetype w:st="on">River</st1:placetype></st1:place>, located in the bustling commercial and shopping centers in Daoli District. It takes a-35-minute drive from the airport and a-15-minute drive from the railway station.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">Harbin Shangri-La<v:shapetype id="_x0000_t75" stroked="f" filled="f" path="m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe" o:preferrelative="t" o:spt="75" coordsize="21600,21600"> <v:stroke joinstyle="miter"></v:stroke><v:formulas><v:f eqn="if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0"></v:f><v:f eqn="sum @0 1 0"></v:f><v:f eqn="sum 0 0 @1"></v:f><v:f eqn="prod @2 1 2"></v:f><v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelWidth"></v:f><v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelHeight"></v:f><v:f eqn="sum @0 0 1"></v:f><v:f eqn="prod @6 1 2"></v:f><v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelWidth"></v:f><v:f eqn="sum @8 21600 0"></v:f><v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelHeight"></v:f><v:f eqn="sum @10 21600 0"></v:f></v:formulas><v:path o:connecttype="rect" gradientshapeok="t" o:extrusionok="f"></v:path><o:lock aspectratio="t" v:ext="edit"></o:lock></v:shapetype><v:shape id="_x0000_s1026" type="#_x0000_t75" style="margin-top: 101.4pt; z-index: 1; left: 0px; margin-left: 207pt; width: 207pt; position: absolute; height: 163.8pt; text-align: left; mso-position-horizontal-relative: text; mso-position-vertical-relative: text"><v:imagedata o:title="2009012408492677835" src="file:///C:\\DOCUME~1\\ADMINI~1\\LOCALS~1\\Temp\\msohtml1\\01\\clip_image001.jpg"></v:imagedata><w:wrap type="square"></w:wrap></v:shape>Hotel offers the best service. It provides 346 elegantly decorated and comfortable guest rooms, 43 of which are suites (president suites included). All suites and riverview rooms can appreciate a spectacular bird''s eye view of the majestic landscape of the <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:placename w:st="on">Songhua</st1:placename> <st1:placetype w:st="on">River</st1:placetype></st1:place> and the Ice and Snow World. Three-Horizon Club floors are available. Every room has Internet interface. The hotel&rsquo;s sophisticated water treatment system ensures that the water in the room can be drunk directly. The 1,350 square meters&rsquo; luxurious grand ballroom can accommodate over one thousand people, enjoying advanced simultaneous interpretation facilities for conference and banquet. Recreational facilities like tennis courts, gymnasium, and swimming pool are readily available.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; color: black; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><img style="width: 469px; height: 342px" alt="" src="/userfiles/image/2009/10/19/2009-10-19-99359.jpg" /></span></span></span></p>', NULL, 90, 1, '/userfiles/image/2009/10/19/2009-10-19-99359.jpg'),
(439, 3, 'Shining', 52, '', '2009-10-19 15:20:34', '2009-10-19 15:20:34', 'Web', 'About Sofitel Wanda Harbin', '', '<p><img height="303" width="479" alt="" src="/userfiles/image/2009/10/19/2009-10-19-11484.jpg" /></p>\r\n<p><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">Sofitel Wanda Harbin is a five-star luxury hotel invested by Dalian Wanda Group and managed by Accor Hotel Management Group. Hotels under operations of the two parties include Sofitel Wanda Chengdu, Sofitel Wanda Beijing, and Sofitel Wanda Harbin. As the largest hospitality management and tourism group in the world, Accor is making influences upon the market of hospitality industry in <st1:country-region w:st="on">China</st1:country-region> with its size and management mode, leading hospitality industry in <st1:city w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">Harbin</st1:place></st1:city> and making excellent service and true hospitality well received. Founded in 1967, as one of the world''s largest hospitality management and tourism group, Accor has developed into a global group that operates over 4000 hotels in 140 countries from economy hotels to luxury hotels including Sofitel, Novotel, Mercure, and Ibis, etc.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><img style="width: 483px; height: 333px" alt="" src="/userfiles/image/2009/10/19/2009-10-19-58662.jpg" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">Located in Harbin Economic Development Zone, Sofitel Wanda Harbin provides 322 guest rooms (suite deluxe included), delicious Asian specialty, dining halls of French, Japanese and Chinese style, 2 bars, 600 square meters&rsquo; multi-functional banquet hall and meeting rooms, as well as recreational facilities and service like gymnasium, swimming pool and spa. It is an elegantly decorated business hotel with elegance, delicacies, and harmony of <st1:country-region w:st="on">China</st1:country-region> and <st1:country-region w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">France</st1:place></st1:country-region>, where true hospitality is to be expected. The modern atmosphere from elaborate designing, magnificent art treasures, together with delicacies and wine ensure you a time of luxury and peace. The moment you check in Sofitel Wanda Harbin, a wonderland unfolds before you!</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: 宋体; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-CN; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><img height="220" width="330" alt="" src="/userfiles/image/2009/10/19/2009-10-19-76756.jpg" /></span></span></p>', NULL, 104, 1, '/userfiles/image/2009/10/19/2009-10-19-76756.jpg'),
(440, 3, 'Shining', 53, 'visa,application,instruction', '2009-10-27 11:28:50', '2009-10-27 11:34:51', 'Carrol', 'Visa_application_instruction', '', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span style="color: black; line-height: 150%"><span style="font: 7pt ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><b><span style="color: black; line-height: 150%">Application Requirement:</span></b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div style="line-height: 150%"><span style="color: black; line-height: 150%">Generally, the following documents should be submitted when applying for Chinese visa: </span></div>\r\n<div style="text-indent: 24pt; line-height: 150%">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="margin: 2.25pt 0cm 2.25pt 18pt; layout-grid-mode: char; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 150%"><span style="color: black; line-height: 150%">1.<span style="font: 7pt ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style="color: black; line-height: 150%">One properly completed visa application form (Ref: <u><a href="/userfiles/2009-10-27-64169.pdf">Visa Application Form</a></u>), which could be obtained from the Chinese Embassy or Consulate-General in person, or by mail with a pre-paid return envelope, or be downloaded from the following website: </span><u><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: blue; line-height: 150%"><a href="http://www.chinaembassycanada.org/">www.chinaembassycanada.org</a></span></u><span style="color: black; line-height: 150%">. No item should be&nbsp;blank&nbsp;or alterd.</span></div>\r\n<div style="margin: 2.25pt 0cm 2.25pt 18pt; layout-grid-mode: char; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 150%"><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: black; line-height: 150%">2.<span style="font: 7pt ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style="color: black; line-height: 150%">One recently taken 2X2 inch photo showing entire face and without a hat on. Please affix the photo to the application form.</span></div>\r\n<div style="margin: 2.25pt 0cm 2.25pt 18pt; layout-grid-mode: char; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 150%"><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: black; line-height: 150%">3.<span style="font: 7pt ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style="color: black; line-height: 150%">Original passport with at least 2 blank visa pages and valid for at least 6 months beyond the date of application.</span></div>\r\n<div style="margin: 2.25pt 0cm 2.25pt 18pt; layout-grid-mode: char; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 150%"><span style="color: black; line-height: 150%">4.<span style="font: 7pt ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style="color: black; line-height: 150%">You are also suggested to bring invitation letter (will be provided by HEU), hotel reservation sheet and flight schedule when you are applying for a Chinese visa.</span></div>\r\n<div style="margin: 2.25pt 0cm 2.25pt 18pt; layout-grid-mode: char; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 150%"><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: black; line-height: 150%">5.<span style="font: 7pt ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style="color: black; line-height: 150%">Former Chinese visa&nbsp;records (if any, together with their copies).</span></div>\r\n<div style="margin: 2.25pt 0cm 2.25pt 18pt; layout-grid-mode: char; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 150%"><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: black; line-height: 150%">6.<span style="font: 7pt ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style="color: black; line-height: 150%">An applicant born in China who is applying for a Chinese visa with his or her new foreign passport is required to submit his or her Chinese passport or last foreign passport.</span></div>\r\n<div style="margin: 2.25pt 0cm 2.25pt 18pt; layout-grid-mode: char; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 150%"><span style="color: black; line-height: 150%">7.<span style="font: 7pt ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style="color: black; line-height: 150%">Other additional documents deemed necessary by the visa officer.</span></div>\r\n<div style="margin: 2.25pt 0cm; layout-grid-mode: char; line-height: 150%">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span style="color: black; line-height: 150%"><span style="font: 7pt ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;</span></span><b><span style="color: black; line-height: 150%">Processing Duration</span></b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div style="margin: 2.25pt 0cm; line-height: 150%"><span style="color: black; line-height: 150%">Visa processing takes 4 working days. For special cases, rush service may be available, but applicants need to pay the extra rush service fee.</span></div>\r\n<div style="margin: 2.25pt 0cm; line-height: 150%">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><b><span style="color: black">Visa-free entry for visitors</span></b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div><span style="color: black">No visa is required for ordinary passport holders from Singapore ,Brunei and Japan to visit China for up to 15 days for business, sightseeing, visiting relatives and friends or transit.</span></div>\r\n<div style="line-height: 150%">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><b><span style="color: black; line-height: 150%">Tips:</span></b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div style="layout-grid-mode: char; line-height: 125%" align="left"><span style="color: black; line-height: 125%">1. Please arrange your travel to China properly before submitting your visa application. Applicants are required to fill in the Visa Application Form completely and correctly, especially the utmost duration of each stay and intended number of entries.</span></div>\r\n<div style="layout-grid-mode: char; line-height: 125%" align="left"><span style="color: black; line-height: 125%">2. Consuls will make the final decision on categories, number of entries and validity and duration of stay according to laws and regulations. </span></div>\r\n<div style="layout-grid-mode: char; line-height: 125%" align="left"><span style="color: black; line-height: 125%">3. Applicants should hold the responsibility to check the contents of visas, and report to consuls when doubts aroused.</span></div>\r\n<div style="layout-grid-mode: char; line-height: 125%" align="left"><span style="color: black; line-height: 125%">4. All foreign citizens should have valid visas when they enter into China. Please check if the visas are valid and have enough number of entries. Applicants should reapply for visas if visas are invalid or numbers of entries is not enough.</span></div>\r\n<div style="layout-grid-mode: char; line-height: 125%" align="left"><span style="color: black; line-height: 125%">5. All foreign citizens should not stay in China beyond the duration of stay permitted.</span></div>\r\n<div style="layout-grid-mode: char; line-height: 125%" align="left"><span style="color: black; line-height: 125%">6. Learn about Chinese visas (Ref: <u><a href="/userfiles/2009-10-27-46288.pdf">Visa Sample</a></u>).</span></div>\r\n<div style="layout-grid-mode: char; line-height: 125%" align="left"><span style="color: black; line-height: 125%">　　　</span><span style="color: black; line-height: 125%">&nbsp; 1) Validity of Visa (Enter before) means that you may use the visa to enter into China before 12:00am on the date printed on the visa if there is enough number of entries.. Visas become invalid and can not be extended after the date of Enter Before&nbsp;even if there are Entries left.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div style="layout-grid-mode: char; line-height: 125%" align="left"><span style="color: black; line-height: 125%">　　　</span><span style="color: black; line-height: 125%">&nbsp; 2) Duration of Each Stay after Entry means the longest period the applicants are permitted to stay in China. Duration of Each Stay is counted from the date of entry. Applicants should apply for an extension of the duration at a local county level Public Security Bureau if he or she stays in China longer than the Duration of Each Stay printed on the visa. </span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', NULL, 37, 1, ''),
